title: long island clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans according to package directions.
Make the sauce by blending flour into the melted butter and then gradually adding the milk.
While stirring, season with salt and pepper and cook until smooth.
Add grated cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Place beans in 1-quart casserole dish and pour sauce over.
Top with crumbled crisp bacon.

title: caramel apple cheese pie(reduced fat)
directions: In mixing bowl beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy and well blended.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
the
butter
and sugar.	Add eggs (well beaten). Add mashed
bananas.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in regular bread tin.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Alternate flour and milk, beating after each addition.
Add baking powder and beat.
Add flavorings. Pour into well greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain.
Mix other ingredients together.
Put into casserole dish.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade shake and make oven frying mix for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large cooking bag.
Shake well to mix.
Moisten chicken in tomato juice before shaking it.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Trim the green and pink from rind of 1 watermelon.
Cut rind in 1-inch cubes; boil until just tender, not soft.
Drain.
Make syrup of the remaining ingredients.
Bring syrup to boil and pour over rind.
Let stand overnight.
Drain, reheat syrup and pour over rind.

title: angel food surprise
directions: Tear cake into small pieces; put in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix pudding as directed on package using the 2 cups milk.
Let stand to thicken.
Fold topping into pudding.
Spread over cake pieces. Cover pudding with pie filling.
Best made a day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; mix well. Combine remaining ingredients; add to bean mixture.
Stir well. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 10 servings.

title: blue ribbon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except rice.
Fold rice into mixture until thoroughly mixed.
Serve warm or cover, refrigerate and serve cold. Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Slice onions round to cover bottom of casserole.
Cut green peppers in pieces and put on top of onions.
Put carrots on top of peppers.
Put cooked spaghetti on top of peppers.
Cover with ground beef.
Pour tomato sauce all over.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: diane's microwave caramel corn
directions: In a large bowl, mix brown sugar, syrup, margarine and salt. Microwave until it boils.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add soda and stir. Put popped corn in a large brown paper bag.
Pour hot caramel mixture over corn.
(Be careful this is very hot.)
Shake the bag to coat the corn.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Shake the bag and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour out on a cookie sheet to cool.

title: 4th of july baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot.
Top with bacon slices.
Cook on high for 45 minutes.
Then cook on low heat for 30 minutes, simmering.

title: corn meal crust chicken pot pie
directions: Cook potatoes and vegetables in chicken broth until tender. Thicken with flour.
Stir in cut up chicken.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Mix Jiffy mix with milk and egg.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until crust is golden and mixture is hot and bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: sweet, sour salad dressing
directions: Mix all together and shake, shake, shake!

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Freeze the head of cabbage for 3 days.
Thaw thoroughly and cut off leaves.
Trim thick center vein of each leaf.
Brown onion in olive oil.
Add to meat, seasonings and rice; mix well.
Place a tablespoon of filling on each cabbage leaf and roll, tucking in edges.
Place rolls in large Dutch oven.
Add enough water so that rolls are 2/3 covered in water.
Arrange sauerkraut on top; add tomato juice.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.
Pour sour cream on top and cook 5 more minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: onion burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, salt and pepper.
Shape into 12 thin patties.
Brown chopped onion lightly in butter; add horseradish, mustard and salt.
Spread onion mixture over 6 patties; top each with a patty and press together to form 6 large patties. Chill. Place patties on grill and brown each side 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve on buns, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Freeze.
Thaw to a slush and add ginger ale and serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck adding chili powder while cooking. Drain and cool. Stir chopped onions, pepper and tomatoes, stir into undrained beans and dressing.
Let stand 2 hours. Add meat and cheese. When ready to serve add lettuce and doritos.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour gradually, beating well.
Mix flavoring.
Slowly stir in 7-Up.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 40 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: potato dill soup
directions: Peel potatoes; cook with onions in boiling water until they begin to fall apart.
Strain.
Add scallions, dill, butter, heavy cream and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup sour cream and let it heat through for 2 minutes.
Garnish each bowl with pepper, dill, parsley and 1 teaspoon sour cream.

title: tomato preserves 2
directions: Wash tomatoes; cover with boiling water and let stand until skins can be easily removed.
Peel.
Cover with sugar and let stand overnight.
Pour off syrup and boil until quite thick and clear; skim.
Slice lemon thin and then add tomatoes, lemon and ginger to syrup.
Cook until tomatoes are clear and thick.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: greenwood high school pizzaburgers
directions: Cook ground beef until done; drain well.
Add soup, pizza sauce, oregano and salt.
Put evenly on hamburger buns.
Top with slice of cheese.
Bake at 300° until cheese melts.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put water in baking dish.
Peel and core apples and slice crosswise into dish.
Mix thoroughly flour, sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Pour over apples and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken feed
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt. Cook until bubbly, then boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in soda. In large bowl, combine Cheerios, raisins, peanuts and M&M's. Pour syrup over mixture; mix to coat and place on greased jellyroll pan. Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage lightly and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix butter with 5 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Add sifted flour and nuts.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, brown sugar, butter and milk to a boil in saucepan.
Cook for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and peanut butter; stir until well melted. Pour into buttered dish, 8 x 8-inch. Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24 squares.

title: microwave sweet and sour shrimp casserole(cooking time:  14 to 16 minutes)
directions: Combine oil, onion and green pepper in 3-quart micro-proof casserole.
Cover.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Set aside.
Pour reserved pineapple syrup into bowl.
Stir in cornstarch and all remaining ingredients except water chestnuts and pineapple.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes, stirring twice during cooking time.
Add shrimp, water chestnuts and pineapple chunks.
Cook on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Add spices to water; heat to boiling.
Add tea and steep 5 minutes.
Heat the fruit juices and sugar just to a boil.
Add to hot tea.
Serve hot or cold.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese and cream.
Blend in mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Combine fruits, pecans and sugar.
Stir cream cheese-mayonnaise mixture into fruits.
Fold fruit mixture into whipped cream.
Pour into freezing tray.
Freeze in refrigerator freezing compartment without stirring.
Serve on lettuce, garnished with cherry halves or pecan halves.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and cocktail sauce.
Add onion salt and garlic powder to taste.
Chop shrimp into medium size pieces.
Mix into dip.
(Save 10 to 15 whole shrimp to decorate the top, if desired.)
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Great with crackers or wafers.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Using a sharp knife, split the unshelled shrimp through, lengthwise, almost to the tail, leaving the feet and tail intact. Remove the veins and pat shrimp dry with paper towel.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pack firmly into an ungreased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Blend in 1 cup sugar and flour; mix into the melted chocolate.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook for 20 minutes until thick.
Cover; cook 10 minutes.
Separate eggs, reserving whites for the meringue.
Place yolks in mixing bowl; beat with a fork.
Add remaining 1/3 cup sugar; add this to chocolate mixture.
Return to heat of double boiler; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, margarine and vanilla.
Set aside to cool.
Set oven at 350°.
Pour filling into 9-inch prebaked pie shell.
Top with meringue; bake until golden brown.

title: muffeletta mix
directions: Serve on French rolls along with Swiss cheese, ham, salami, pastrami, mayonnaise and mustard.

title: christmas cobbler with pear 'n cranberries
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan, combine first three ingredients.
Stir in cranberries. Heat to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes or until cranberries pop open.
Stir in pears.
Pour into pan.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats; mix well.
Add egg, mixing until moistened.
Crumble evenly over fruit.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel and halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash well with fork.
Add dressing mixture and vinegar.
Cream together until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Scoop into egg halves. Garnish with paprika, olives, radishes or fresh herbs as desired.

title: green bean and mushroom casserole
directions: Alternate beans and onions in layers in a 1-quart casserole. Mix everything else but cheese and pour over beans.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(cholesterol free)
directions: Melt margarine in an 8-inch round microwave-safe dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple and cherries on top.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes on low speed. Spread batter over fruit.
Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes (ovens vary).
Invert cake onto serving plate.
Let stand over cake a few minutes.
Serve warm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots until tender, drain and cool. Slice onions; mix well with carrots.
Mix mustard and sugar together.
Stir in oil, vinegar and tomato juice.
Pour over carrots and onions.
Cover and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: corn flake chews
directions: Combined Sugar and syrup in large boiler.
Stir constantly. When this starts to boil, boil for 1 minutes. Take off heat and add peanut butter, stir until it melts.
Add corn flakes and stir until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls quickly onto wax paper.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes to a full boil.
After boiling begins, try not to stir unless it starts to burn.
When temperature gets around 290°, turn heat down to medium-low.
Boil until it reaches 306°.

title: christmas molded salad
directions: Prepare gelatin. Add fruit, nuts and relish. Let mold in refrigerator.
Serve
on lettuce.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: fruited pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in a Dutch oven; pour off drippings.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper; add apple juice, water and cinnamon sticks.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add apricots, prunes and apple (peeled and sliced).
Cover and cook an additional 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in sheet cake pan.
Season as desired.
Make stuffing.
Place 1 scoop of stuffing on each pork chop.
Make gravy and pour over pork chops. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: fruitcake
directions: Add spices to flour, salt and soda and add to mixture of oleo (melted or softened), sugar, eggs and milk.
Pour over fruit and nuts.
Bake in 275° oven for about 3 hours, until well done, top springs back when touched and toothpick comes out clean.
Place a pan of water in oven under pan.
Use tube pan.
Makes about 8 pounds of fruitcake.
Needs to be cooked two to three weeks before eating.
Let cake cool completely before removing from pan.
I put a piece of brown paper in bottom of greased pan with grease on paper.
This helps to get cake out of pan.

title: martha patch's ozark pudding
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add lemon rind.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add, beating after every addition.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pare and cut apples into slices. Place over batter and top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with topping of 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup chopped nuts over the top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 9.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add corn meal last.
Pour into your favorite baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: corned beef cabbage casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, cabbage, onion and crumbled corned beef in shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with celery soup.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Cook beef in oil to brown.
Stir in 1 cup of water and spices.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in barley, 4 cups water, carrots, celery, onions, tomato sauce and broth.
Heat to boiling. Simmer until carrots are crisp and tender, about 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour with soda added to the last 1/2 cup flour.
Add this to creamed mixture along with buttermilk. Add lemon extract.
Bake at 350° in skillet for 30 minutes.

title: cherry swim
directions: Pick good ripe cherries.
Clean and crush seeds and all.
Mix in this sugar.
Put into a large jar.
Add whiskey or bourbon. Seal and set aside.
Shake every day once for 4 weeks.
When cherries sink, it's ready to use or let set for a month.
Strain liquid into bottle.
Gets better with age.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients except Mozzarella.
Layer half the noodles in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; spread with half cheese mixture.
Add half Mozzarella and half meat sauce; repeat.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes (or assemble early and refrigerate; bake 45 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cloud nine salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and pineapple syrup.
Add drained pineapple and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in loaf pan or make pone and put on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: christine's pickles
directions: Pack clean cucumbers into jars with a sprig of dill, a slice of onion, a wedge of green pepper, hot pepper, several buds of garlic and grape leaves.
Add 1/4 teaspoon of alum into each jar. Mix the water, vinegar and salt well.
Pour brine over pickles and process in a water bath until the pickles start to turn color.
Be sure they are hot as the jars seal better.

title: peach berry betty
directions: Stir together sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg. Stir in juice or water; toss to coat. Add 2 cups bread cubes. Toss until mixed. Transfer to an ungreased 2-quart square pan.

title: crown of gold tuna casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with 2 packages of cheese.
Put in greased pan.
Beat egg whites and fold in 1 package of cheese. Spoon on top and spread.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve about 8.

title: mom's scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Crush an additional 1/2 cup cracker crumbs along with 1 tablespoon melted butter to spread over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 4.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes and put into a boiling pot. Coarsely chop onion and add to the potatoes. Cover with water and add enough water to come up over the potatoes about a couple inches. Salt to taste. Cook until the potatoes are very tender and the onions are clear. Remove from the heat and add just enough milk to change the color of the liquid to white. Don't add the milk while the liquid is still boiling or you will have a
bad result. I take a hand potato masher and mash the potatoes a little to thicken the liquid some. When poured into bowls, pepper to suit taste.

title: celery seed deli slaw
directions: Cut cabbage in very thin shreds (don't use white fiberous part).

title: reduced calorie trifle
directions: Bake or buy an angel food cake.
Prepare sugar-free pudding as directed on package.
Crumble 1/3 of the angel food cake into a trifle bowl.
Next, layer with 1/3 of the pudding and then 1/3 of the light Cool Whip.
Put a layer of sliced strawberries on top of the Cool Whip.
Repeat 2 times.
On the last layer, use whole or halved strawberries.

title: cinnamon jumbles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
(To make buttermilk, replace 1 tablespoon of milk with vinegar.)
Sift together and stir in flour, soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Drop teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on lightly greased pan. Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake until set but not brown.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: summer apple pudding
directions: Place apples in a shallow 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle half the sugar and cinnamon over the apples.
Cream butter and rest of sugar until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls of dough over apples and spread with spatula.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: lemon coconut cookies
directions: Cream the butter with the granulated sugar until light and fluffy; beat in lemon zest, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add flour and salt; beat mixture until it forms a dough.
Add coconut. Chill dough 1 hour.
Halve the dough on a sheet of wax paper. Form each half into an 8-inch log.
Chill the logs for 4 hours or overnight.

title: south texas bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for cheese and chips. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into patties.
Brown on each side. Place in Pyrex dish and cover with prepared gravy.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fantasy freeze pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme; mix well.
Add sherbet; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust shell.
Top with almonds.
Freeze until firm.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Mix together in a large baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until desired thickness, stirring occasionally.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except corn flakes and butter. Pour into a 9 x 14-inch casserole. Crush the corn flakes.
Mix with butter.
Spread on top of casserole. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°, slowly and a long time.
Good for a potluck, buffet or any large group.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla thoroughly. Measure flour by dip-level, pour method or by sifting. Blend soda and salt with flour. Mix in nuts and chocolate pieces. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet. Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low flame until thick.
Cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in strawberries. Put in refrigerator until almost set.
Remove and beat with electric beater.
Fold in Cool Whip and cake pieces.
Pour in spring-form pan and return to refrigerator until firm.
Garnish with fresh strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mix stuffing and melted oleo.
Mix soup, sour cream and water chestnuts. Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer with stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: vegetarian gravy
directions: Melt the margarine in a large skillet.
Crack an egg (unbeaten) into the melted butter.
With a fork, immediately begin to scramble the egg.
Stir constantly until the egg is cooked and is in very tiny pieces.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of flour on the mixture; stir. Let the mixture bubble for about 10 seconds, but do not brown or burn.

title: *chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Place broccoli in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Boil chicken for 5 minutes; bone chicken and remove skin.
Break into pieces and place over broccoli.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry. Pour soup mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with grated cheese and toasted bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Marinate chicken overnight.
Place chicken and water in 5-quart pot and boil until tender.
Remove chicken; cool, bone and chop.
Pour stock in a bowl and refrigerate 1 hour.
Skim fat off; measure 2 cups and discard.
Preheat oven to 350° in 2-quart pot; mix together picante sauce, stock, soup and 1/2 cup cheese.
Heat until boiling, stirring occasionally.
Dip tortilla in sauce; scrape off excess on side of pot.
In bottom, put 1/3 of tortilla; place 2 tablespoons chicken, 2 tablespoons sour cream and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Roll filled tortilla and place rolled side down in a greased baking pan.
Continue until all tortillas are used; pour remainder of sauce over enchiladas; top with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with green onions.

title: stuffed baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet. Saute onion until tender.
Add bread crumbs, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Layer stuffing mixture evenly in 8 x 8-inch baking dish sprayed with butter flavored cooking spray.
Place fillets on top of stuffing.
Melt 2 teaspoons margarine.
Drizzle over fish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serves 4.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put all in mixing bowl.
Mix with mixer.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Cut cheese into 1-inch cubes.
Cook broccoli several minutes.
Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl and stir until mixed.
Pour into a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ardsheal house cheese soup
directions: Heat the butter in a saucepan and saute onion until wilted. Add the crumbled cheeses, sprinkle on the flour and cook, stirring, about 2 minutes.
Remove from stove and gradually add the liquids and seasonings.
Return to heat and bring the soup to a boil, then simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove the bay leaf and thin the soup with a little milk if desired.
Serves 8.

title: dessert kolacky(a polish dessert from monica's family)
directions: Thoroughly blend margarine, softened cream cheese and sugar. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Knead to form stiff dough.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness on well-floured board.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves in center; press opposite corners together.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sweet-n-sour pork
directions: Heat cooking oil in frypan.
Thoroughly brown pork, sprinkle well with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Add onion and pineapple.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Add tomato wedges; blend cornstarch with sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple syrup.
Add to mixture.
Stir constantly until thick. Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve over a nest of boiled rice.

title: old fashioned navy bean soup
directions: Clean and wash beans.
Combine water, beans, ham bone and seasoning.
Cook on low heat 4 to 5 hours.
Dice vegetables.
Add to beans after they have cooked about 4 hours or almost done. Turn heat to high and bring to boil, then turn to low for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: florida clam chowder
directions: Peel and slice onions.
Fry in butter.
Add hot water to potatoes (ground).
Boil until soft.
Add clams; season with salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in a well-greased pan for 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Warm milk and butter; blend flour, salt and sugar.
Add corn, well beaten eggs and milk.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 450°.

title: microwave chili chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of the chips in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Drain the chicken and spread over the corn chips.
Layer the onion, chilies and cheese slices over the chicken.
Cover with remaining corn chips and top with soup diluted with the water.
(If desired, add more cheese on top.) Cover and cook in microwave oven for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish after 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Mash cookies; melt butter and combine with cookie crumbs.
Put in bottom of 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator and let set 1 hour.
(Remember to save 1/2 crumbs for top.) Combine softened cream cheese with one carton Cool Whip.
Beat very well and put over crumbs that were refrigerated.
Let set 1 hour.
Make chocolate pudding and cool and pour over.
Let set 1 hour.
Put on second tub of Cool Whip and sprinkle rest of cookie crumbs. Refrigerate and let set 1 hour.
Outrageous dessert.

title: white corn salad
directions: Combine ingredients in the order listed.
This is best if made the day before you plan to serve it.
The salad is very colorful and can be increased to serve a crowd.

title: creamy cauliflower salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in medium bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over veggies.
Toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown chops in heavy casserole with lid.
Layer 3 chops then half of each vegetables in order of carrots, potatoes, onions and peppers.
Pour 1/2 of soup; repeat process.
Put vinegar, salt, pepper and cayenne into soup can to rinse out.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake slowly at 200° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Soak cod fish in water for 2 hours.
Shred cod fish into a bowl.
Cut tomatoes into cubes along with avocado.
Dice onions. Mix all together with 2 teaspoons of oil.
Serve chilled with Italian bread.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Place bread in 9-inch round glass dish.
Heat milk and margarine on High 3 minutes in 4-cup measure.
Stir small amount of hot milk into beaten eggs.
Return eggs to milk.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and raisins.
Pour mixture over bread pieces.
Cook on High 7 minutes.
Cook 2 minutes longer, if center is not firm.

title: quick corn light bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add buttermilk.
Grease loaf pan.
Heat shortening until very hot.
Add to batter.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let cool at least 30 minutes in pan.

title: turkey salad
directions: Chop turkey breast into bite size pieces and chop eggs.
Mix all ingredients.
Add more mayonnaise if necessary to get the right consistency.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil sugar and water. Add cranberries and cook until they pop. Stir in dry jello. After it starts to gel, add apples, oranges and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: low calorie spinach lasagne
directions: Spray pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Brown ground meat. Remove, reserving 1 teaspoon drippings.
Add onions; saute.
Add garlic.
Cook 1 minute, then add beef; blend in oregano, tomato puree, basil, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes. Cook noodles; drain.
Mix spinach (water removed), cottage cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
In 9-inch square pan, place 1/3 spinach mix on bottom.
Use 2 noodles to make a layer; spread meat sauce, continue layering.
Cover with foil. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Add sugar, coconut and coconut milk or water to egg whites. Cook over low heat to full boil, then for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and spread on cake while frosting and cake is still warm. (Do not use any other kind of coconut except fresh frozen; the other kind has sugar on them and will crystallize.)

title: country chicken
directions: Brown chicken in Crisco (I like to roll chicken in Progresso Italian style bread crumbs).
Put remaining ingredients (except rice) in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Put rice in bottom of baking pan.
Pour 1/2 sauce over; add chicken and pour remaining sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (paprika before baking).

title: creamy summer slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well until blended.
Finely chop small head of cabbage, 2 small zucchini squash and 2 small yellow squash julienne style.
Pour dressing over vegetables and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: gingersnaps(cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, molasses and spices; mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Take 1 rounded teaspoonful of batter and make in ball and roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes (no longer).
Remove from oven and leave on cookie sheet 1 minute before removing to plate or cloth.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; cream together shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add to creamed ingredients egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a solid candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes and sugar.
Blend with 3 cups Bisquick (reserve remaining cup of Bisquick).
Stir in milk. Mixture will be sticky.
Cover bowl with dish towel for 1/2 hour. Spread remaining cup of Bisquick on waxed paper.
Scrape mixture from bowl on top of Bisquick and knead lightly.
Pat with ball of hand to 1-inch thickness.
Cut out with medium glass, dipping glass or cutter each time in remaining Bisquick.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 biscuits.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add everything else. Beat well with mixer. Pour into unbaked 9-inch
pie crust. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until set.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Cook in saucepan the oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the flour and sugar to this mixture. Add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in a greased and floured baking sheet (12 x 18 x 1-inch) for 20 minutes at 350°.
Ice the cake while still warm.

title: twinkie torte
directions: Melt chips in sugar and water.	Let cool.
Cut Twinkies in thirds lengthwise.	Lay half on bottom of 9-inch torte pan.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil. Add sugar and maple flavoring, stir until dissolved. Cook for 2 minutes.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Mix everything together and cook until soft.
If you use a double boiler, it cooks it best.

title: sharon's delight
directions: In a 9x13 inch pan bake cake according to directions.
When cool, punch holes with toothpick in the cake.
In a saucepan mix sugar and pineapple and boil for 5 minutes.
When cool, pour over cake.
Mix vanilla pudding and pour over top of pineapple.
Slice bananas over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip, then cover with coconut, cherries and pecans.
Keep refrigerated.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into a large bowl.
Beat the egg and combine with vinegar and water.
Cut in shortening and sprinkle with egg and vinegar, then mix all ingredients together.
With dough, form a ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for 30 minutes before using.
This dough can be kept in refrigerator for up to a week.
Or, can divide into 4 parts (1 part makes 1 pie).
Wrap each securely and freeze until ready to use.
Makes 4 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, vinegar, water and salt.
Pour into pie shell.
Over top sprinkle nutmeg and dot with butter. Bake at 350° until mixture is bubbly and crust brown, about 1 hour.

title: sara's dressing
directions: You will need jar with lid.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check often.
Cake will feel heavy in weight.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, to a temperature of 236° on candy thermometer, or until small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into very cold water.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until creamy.
Drop from large spoon onto waxed paper and let stand until firm.
Makes about 1 3/4 pounds.

title: baked turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, green pepper, onions and lemon juice and peel.
Toss lightly.
Stir in mayo.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese and then crushed potato chips. Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate covered cookies
directions: Put peanut butter in middle of Ritz crackers to make a sandwich.
You can also use Ritz Bits crackers or mini or regular size Oreo cookies.

title: homemade dumplings
directions: Boil fryer until done; debone if prefer so.
Mix flour, soda, salt, milk, egg and butter.
Roll out and cut into small squares. Drop dough squares into boiling broth (drop a few at a time to prevent them sticking together).
Mix 2 heaping tablespoons flour with 2 cups milk and add to pot.
Stir gently.
Cover and let set 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage salad supreme
directions: Toast sesame seeds and almonds in a 350° oven.
Mix cabbage, and onions together.
Just before adding the dressing add the sesame seeds, almonds, and uncooked noodles.

title: ham quiche
directions: Mix eggs with mayonnaise, flour and milk.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell which has already been baked. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 475°.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple and strawberries together. Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13 glass dish and let set. Spread sour cream over top. Then pour rest of mixture over sour cream and let set. After it's set, cut into squares and place on lettuce leaf in a salad plate.

title: can can chicken
directions: Mix soup, water and rice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Butter chicken parts and place on rice mixture. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips, and mix well. Pour into casserole dish and top with crushed chips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell; bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate raisin cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: shrimp with oyster sauce
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Chill for half hour.
Heat wok.
Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir-fry celery for 1 minute.
Remove wok from heat.
Remove celery onto plate and wipe wok with paper towel.
Mix chilled shrimp with egg white and 1 tablespoon wine.
Reheat wok. Add remaining oil.
Saute shrimp mixture for 1 minute.
Add remaining wine, salt, sugar and oyster sauce.
Stir-fry quickly and add celery for 15 seconds.
Remove from wok quickly.

title: deep fried mushrooms
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms.
Cut large ones in half. Dip in flour, egg and bread crumbs. Deep fry in oil.

title: chocolate resolution
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a blender; blend until smooth. Garnish with marshmallows.
Serves 1 person.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel, boil and mash eggplants; drain.
Cook meat until done and drain.
Next saute onions and bell pepper and drain.
Combine all ingredients and put in 2 (9 x 13-inch) casserole dishes.
Put in 350° oven and heat thoroughly.

title: old fashioned dark fruitcake
directions: Line loaf pans with wax paper and grease with shortening. Depending on size, it takes 2 to 4 loaf pans.
Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Blend in flour, eggs, salt and baking powder.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, mace, cloves, soda, hot coffee, molasses and jelly.
Blend in raisins, nuts, cherries, mixed candied fruit and rind and juice of one orange and 1 lemon.
Pour into loaf pans and bake at 300° (slow oven) for about 2 1/2 hours. Take out of pans at once and remove wax paper.

title: whiskey sour bowl
directions: Thaw frozen juices and add bitters and sugar, stir until blended.
Stir in whiskey sour cocktail mix and club soda. Garnish with orange and lemon slices and cherries.
Makes 18 (4-ounce) servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add garlic cheese and blend well.
Fold in remaining ingredients, expect the pecans.
Shape into two even balls.
Roll each ball in the crushed pecans.
Serve with vegetable crackers.

title: turkey noodle soup
directions: Cook egg noodles in 4 cups water.
Leave in pot.
Cook celery, salt, pepper, onions.
Add to noodles.
Add turkey and milk.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: taco casserole
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with chips; brown hamburger and drain.
Add water and seasoning; simmer 5 minutes.
Add beans. Pour over chips.
Cover with chilies and taco sauce.
Top with cheese and bake at 400° until cheese melts.
Top with sour cream. May be heated in microwave.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Mix spices, water, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Cut chicken into 1/8-inch slices diagonally, place in sauce; let stand.
Slice onions, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Add snow peas.
Cook on high in 1/4 cup salad oil.
Stir quickly until done (2 to 5 minutes). Remove.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 tablespoons oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Mix chicken and vegetables and serve over rice.

title: melting shortbread
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and whip with a mixer.
Mix flour and cornstarch together and add to butter mixture.
Drop from spoon and press with a fork lightly.
Bake at 325° on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Watch closely, about 8 to 10 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Fry sausage.
Drain.
Mix eggs with a little milk.
Pour over sausage and scrambled eggs.
Put Pizza Quick sauce (half jar) on crust.
Spread cheese and add sausage and eggs. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 18 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding then add cool whip.
Mix cream cheese mixture with pudding mixture.
Add a layer of cookies in bottom of flower pot.
Add mixture, cookies, etc.
Continue until flower pot is full.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
When cool, use wooden spoon handle to make holes in the cake.
Pour Eagle sweetened milk over cake and top with 1 can coconut.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: au gratin vegetables
directions: Blend white sauce and cheese; combine with vegetables.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Toss crumbs with butter; sprinkle atop.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.

title: blueberry cake squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream together shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar in bowl until light and fluffy, using an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Punch holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Combine milk and cream of coconut; pour over cake.
Frost with
Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
(Best if made the day before.)

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat cream cheese in soup and cool.
Add gelatine and celery, onion, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and shrimp together.
Chill for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs (beat well).
Add flour with bananas.
Blend thoroughly.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake 60 minutes at 350°. Let bread cool in pan 20 minutes.

title: cranberry apple jello salad
directions: Mix jellos as per directions on package, but use 1 cup less water.
The juice of the pineapple is used instead.
Add canned cranberries; break up in jello.
Add fresh cranberries and chopped apples.
Add pineapple and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; refrigerate until set.
Cut into 2-inch squares to serve.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together and heat until cheese is melted.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla, evaporated milk and cottage cheese until fluffy.
Make crust with graham crackers and oleo; mix well.
Sprinkle some graham cracker crumbs on top of filling after filling is put in crust (in pie pan or cake pan).
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: taco dip
directions: Lay lettuce leaves on platter. Spread bean dip over lettuce. Mash avocados up. Spread over bean dip. Mix sour cream with taco mix. Spread over avocados. Top with diced onions, black olives (sliced) and tomatoes; end with your choice of grated cheese.

title: mom's delicious green beans
directions: Spray pot with Pam and put on a low fire.
Put bacon in pot. Let bacon cook until done, but not crisp.
Pour off some of the grease. Add chopped onion and potatoes.
Cook until slightly browned.
Add green beans. Cook until beans are done. Add salt and pepper to suit your taste.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese and a few drops Worcestershire sauce. Spread out on tray. Spread the shrimp over that.
Spread the shrimp cocktail sauce over that.
Serve with crackers. Can add minced onion to cream cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
Blend dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, butter, oil and sugar, then add eggs and dry ingredients.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
Make into balls the size of a walnut.
Butter the bottom of a flat bottom glass.
Dip glass in sugar and flatten ball of dough.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 7 dozen.
Great for Christmas cookies with colored sugar.

title: light egg nog
directions: In large saucepan, over medium heat, heat 5 cups milk, egg substitute and sugar until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and rum extracts.
Cover; chill.
Just before serving, stir in brandy, if desired.
Thin to desired consistency with remaining skim milk.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Yeild; 8 servings.
Per serving, 128 calories, 0 grams fat.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Peel the asparagus stalks and cut them into little pieces, reserving a few whole tips for garnish.
Peel the potatoes and cut into small cubes.
They thicken and bind the soup.
Peel and wash the leeks, slice them crosswise and saute them gently in butter in a large saucepan.
Season with salt and maggi arome to taste.
The leeks intensify the flavor of the soup.
Add the asparagus and potatoes and briefly saute.
Add the milk and water.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; allow to rest briefly. Meanwhile, blanch the reserved tips.
Puree the soup in a food processor or blender or puree by hand.
Add the cream and the pat of butter.
Season with pepper to taste and stir gently.
Pour the soup into a serving bowl.
Garnish with the asparagus tips.
Serves 4.

title: yummy baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, add to the other ingredients and bake.

title: pink applesauce
directions: In a bowl, sprinkle applesauce with cinnamon.
Mix jello with boiling water.
Add warm to applesauce.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots (just barely tender).
Drain and cool; add onion and pepper.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour all over carrots. Let set 12 hours in refrigerator.
Drain all liquid.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep 2 or 3 months.
Reserve liquid.
May be used for another batch of carrots.

title: cold tuna casserole
directions: Stir all together, but do not put potatoes in until ready to serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Cool.
Cover the bottom of a small bowl with vanilla wafers.
Place a layer of sliced bananas to cover the wafers and then a layer of pudding. Repeat all layers.
Refrigerate.

title: good punch
directions: Mix Jello according to package directions. Add lemonade and water, pineapple juice and apricot nectar. Add ginger ale when ready to serve punch.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients together. Layer in dish. Place grated cheese on top. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: winter fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package; overlap and press onto 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet or pizza pan (flour fingers if needed to prevent sticking).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely

title: never fail divinity
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil for only 2 minutes.
Place marshmallow cream in large bowl and pour hot syrup all at once into it.
Stir until candy loses its gloss, then add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Melt chips and paraffin.
Add together.
Drop balls in chocolate.
Put on wax paper.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Can use 1 cup lemon juice instead of coconut.
Lightly grease 9 1/4-inch or 10 1/2-inch pan.
Put all ingredients in blender on high for 15 seconds.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook vegetables for 10 minutes in 1/2 cup water.
Layer meat and vegetables in buttered casserole; top with soup and bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and dice; cook until soft.
Mash.
Add all ingredients.
Stir, make soft.

title: poached salmon with zucchini
directions: Spray large saucepan with cooking spray.
Place salmon in saucepan.
Add milk or wine, water, and chicken flavoring or stock.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until salmon is done, about 6 minutes.
Cut zucchini into small strips and steam for 2-3 minutes.
Pour into a bowl and toss gently with basil.
Transfer to serving plates.
Top with salmon.
Garnish with sprigs of basil.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan. Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.
Drain.
Place potatoes and onion in a bowl. Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Add to the potato mixture; toss gently to coat.
Yields 4 servings (about 69 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini according to pkg. directions. Mix all ingredients together with rotini and refrigerate.

title: african yam fritters
directions: Boil, peel and mash yams.
Beat egg.
Saute tomato, chile and onion in peanut oil until onion is transparent and soft.
Combine sauteed mixture, egg, bread crumbs, seasonings and yams.
Form mixture into patties and brown on both sides.
Eat!
Makes 10 small servings.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Select chops 3/4-inch thick.
Salt and dredge with flour; fry in small amount of oil until brown on both sides.

title: szechuan sesame noodles
directions: Cook 1 pound of linguini in water with 1 tablespoon oil to prevent sticking.
Drain, rinse and add 1 tablespoon oil to toss.

title: fortified milk
directions: Pour liquid milk into blender. Add dry milk. Blend well. Makes 1 quart. Refrigerate.

title: shredded au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in water until almost tender.
Cool, peel and shred to make about 4 cups.
Place in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; sprinkle liberally with onion salt.
Top with cheese; pour milk over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces.
Use only top of broccoli.
Serves 15.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine meat and milk.
Divide into 5 patties.
Pat out to 6-inch circles. Put 1/4 cup stuffing mix in center of each; draw meat over and seal.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Mix well and cook in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: myrtle's taffy
directions: Melt the butter.
Add sugar, hot water and vinegar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil until mixture turns brittle in cold water.
Turn into a well-buttered pan to cool.
Pull until white, then cut into cubes.
(This is a good time to invite friends over to have a "candy making" party and to help each other, also to fellowship.)

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cook in skillet in enough oil to cover the bottom all of the first ingredients until chicken is done, about 10 minutes.
Add second ingredients and mix it all together in skillet.
Roll in tortilla shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° covered in a Pammed pan.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to set.
Add crushed pineapple (drained), chopped nuts and cherries.
Fold in whipping cream.
Return to refrigerator until congealed.

title: orange fudge
directions: In a large kettle melt margarine.
Add cream and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add candy melts and flavoring.
Stir well and pour into large pan.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 2-inch slices.
Combine margarine, sugar and water in a cast-iron skillet; add potatoes.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 1 to 2 hours or until potatoes are done and liquid is thick.
Watch potatoes carefully and turn frequently.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt. Add beaten eggs and drained fruit cocktail.
Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle over the top 1 cup brown sugar and nuts. Bake 1 hour or more until done at 300°.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.

title: hot and spicy pecans
directions: Melt butter, add all ingredients, except pecans.
Stir well. Remove from heat and cool, add pecans.
Stir about 5 minutes, spread on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: canned tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes and pack in jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of sugar.
Put on lids.
Put in oven.
Set oven at 255° for 45 minutes.
Leave tomatoes in oven until cool.

title: choc caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup of the evaporated milk, stirring, over low heat until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine.
Mix well.
Press 1/2 of the cake mixture in the bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup walnuts and the chocolate chips over crust.
Top with caramel mixture, spreading to edges of pan.
Top with teaspoonfuls of the remaining cake mixture.
Press gently.
Sprinkle remaining nuts. Press gently.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars or refrigerate.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate onion and potatoes.
Let stand for 10 minutes and remove liquid.
Mix egg, flour, salt, pepper, baking powder and milk together and pour in with the onion and potatoes.
Drop desired amount into hot oil and fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Mix cream cheese with browned and drained sausage. Cut edges off bread and cut in half.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread halves and roll up jelly roll style.
Cut bacon slice in thirds and wrap 1/3 around bread.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix the popcorn, nuts and M&M's in extra large mixing bowl. Melt slowly the butter, oil and marshmallows; pour over popcorn mixture.
Mix well with large spoon.
Pack in well-greased tube pan.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Dip pan in warm water and loosen with knife.

title: very good pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Then add flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture. Now add sour cream and flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: beef soup
directions: Place meat and bones in a large pot with water.
Let come to a boil.
Skim.
Prepare vegetables by washing, peeling and chopping. Add seasoning and vegetables, except potatoes, and simmer for about 2 1/2 hours.
Add whole potatoes and simmer for another hour.

title: creole chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 1 quart of water until done. Cool and remove meat from bone.
Reserve broth.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Add garlic, red pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Combine Ro-Tel and broth with sauce mixture; simmer 10 minutes.
Add rice and chicken. Cover with tightly fitting lid and simmer for 1 hour.
Add broth as needed.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in large pan over medium heat.
Stir in cocoa. Get it hot, but not boiling.
Stir in the peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Grease foil with butter.
Spread the fudge mixture into pan, pressing well to the edges.
Allow to cool until firm.
Cut into small pieces and store in airtight container.
This recipe is easy to divide into half.

title: grandma klose's stuffed peppers
directions: Mix meat, rice, salt and pepper and stuff into peppers.
Make meat balls out of the remaining mixture to drop into sauce.
Put tomato paste and 2 cans of water into a large kettle.
Add salt and pepper.
(Add 1 teaspoon sugar; optional.)
Put in some ketchup.
Cover kettle and cook slowly at a low temperature for about 2 hours.

title: ginger fruit dip(very nice with sliced pears and apples.)
directions: In a small bowl combine pudding, milk and orange juice and beat 1 minute.
Stir in sour cream and ginger.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.

title: italian green beans
directions: Place green beans, butter and dry dressing in casserole.
Stir occasionally until butter melts.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal, let stand 20 minutes.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apples, cranberries and sugar and put in buttered casserole dish.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add all ingredients and mix well.
Place in ice cream freezer until frozen.

title: quick brunswick stew
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add ham and onion; cook until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, broth, lima beans, corn and potatoes. Cover; cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour over butter (don't stir).
Pour fruit over crust.
Bake until golden brown.

title: potato and spinach soup
directions: Bring broth, water, scallions, potatoes and celery to a boil. In a 4-quart pot, reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Puree in batches in blender or food processor until puree is smooth and bright green, adding some of the spinach to each batch.
Pour into a 3-quart container.
Stir in buttermilk and salt; cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to 2 days.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cook vinegar and sugar until syrupy and pour boiling hot over ingredients slowly.
Let stand 12 to 24 hours.
Mix occasionally. Good with beef or pork.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend together first 7 ingredients.
Add, by hand, the apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.
Can be iced and cut into bars.

title: angie's rice dressing
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add mushrooms, rice and soups. Mix well.
Cover and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover, stir and bake 10 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix butter, onion, garlic and mushroom soup; simmer 15 minutes.
Pour the hot soup mixture over the beans and pimentos. Mix and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until bread crumbs are brown or until the casserole bubbles on the side.

title: ivory coast chicken
directions: Wipe chicken dry; brown in oil 5 to 10 minutes, turning 2 to 3 times.
Add both kinds of onions, tomatoes and tomato paste; cook 1 minute.
Stir in chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Cover and boil 8 minutes.
Turn heat to low.
Mix peanut butter with warm water to make a paste and add this to the chicken.
Add salt, cayenne pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer 30 minutes.
This is very spicy; adjust to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cornflake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Let mixture boil up once. Stir continually.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and cornflakes.
Mix well, working quickly.
Put mixture into greased 12 x 20 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Press down and cut into squares while warm.

title: spaghetti sauce with chicken
directions: Blend stewed tomatoes a few seconds.
Simmer with basil, pepper, brown sugar and olive oil a few minutes.
Fry boneless chicken breasts in olive oil and a pinch of garlic until done. Pour sauce over spaghetti and chicken.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend flour, margarine and powdered sugar well and press into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Blend other ingredients and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes more.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with the sour milk.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine flour and salt; set aside.
Chop dates and nuts, then add butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour to mixture.
When mixed well, roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes in preheated 300° oven.
When done, roll hot ball in confectioners sugar.

title: cheese and bacon canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread) together.
Place about a teaspoon on each piece of bread.
Freeze on cookie sheet, then transfer to freezer container or bake and enjoy immediately.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 60 to 70.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well to blend.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter in
a medium saucepan; stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and
onion.
Add sour cream, stirring until well blended.
Add Swiss cheese; cook, while stirring, until cheese is completely melted.
In
a
greased
3-quart
casserole, add beans and cover
with
cheese
sauce.
Sprinkle
with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake
25 minutes at 350°.
Serve while piping hot.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 3 minutes; set aside.
Cream butter or margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add baking soda, baking powder, spices and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.

title: bran muffins
directions: Use large bowl.
Pour boiling water over cereal to soften. Mix remaining ingredients as usual.
Bake at 350° until done. Makes 5 dozen.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well, then chill.
Roll out thick and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon coconut bars
directions: Mix the cup of flour, butter and powdered sugar as for pie crust.
Pat into an 8 x 8-inch pan, buttered.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: date balls
directions: Put butter, egg and sugar in heavy skillet and cook over low heat until egg is cooked, stirring constantly.
Add dates and continue cooking and stirring until sugar from dates is dissolved. Remove from heat; add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Stir until completely mixed.
Drop by teaspoons into coconut, form into ball.

title: vegetable dressing
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Beat 10 minutes.
Be careful not to underbeat.
This dressing will store in the refrigerator for several weeks.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, apples, flour, salt and soda together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in greased loaf pan for 1 hour until done.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Crumble; reserve.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in bacon drippings until tender.
Add ground beef; cook until well browned, breaking up with fork as it cooks.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Add vegetables; simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, lard and salt.
Beat egg in measuring cup. Work mixture very hard.
Vinegar keeps it from becoming hard. Makes 8 crusts.
Divide and separate with waxed paper.
Freezes very well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Grease and flour a Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon-raisin scone sticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Turn onto surface dusted with baking mix.
Roll in baking mix to coat.
Knead dough 5 times. Roll into rectangle, 10 x 6-inches.
Cut crosswise into ten 1-inch strips.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 sticks.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop by teaspoon into hot deep fat, cook until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: garlic and tomato chicken
directions: In skillet, saute in oil the garlic and spices for about 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients except chicken.
Bring this to a boil, then cover and turn down heat to simmer for 50 minutes. Thicken with cornstarch and water, if
desired.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt; mix.
Add water and vinegar. Add egg.
Add to flour mixture (may not take off the liquid if its a wet day).
Stir only enough to form into a ball.
Divide into 3 balls.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 425°.
Makes 3 pie crusts.
This dough may be frozen and used as needed.

title: shrimp and pasta(serves 4)
directions: *You may substitute your favorite vegetables in place of tomato and/or pepper.

title: chocolate mint snow-top cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt 1 cup of chocolate morsels; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in melted chocolate and vanilla extract.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in the flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup mint chocolate morsels.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap; freeze until firm, about 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Add water and cinnamon.
Stir in pumpkin.
Mix well.

title: pizza cups
directions: Separate biscuits into sections.
Put each piece of dough into greased cupcake tin and form it to shape of pan.
Put 1 tablespoon sauce, then add meat and/or vegetables.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: decorator icing
directions: Dissolve salt in water in large mixing bowl.
Add vanilla, Crisco and sifted powdered sugar in a little at a time, stirring with mixer after each addition.
When all the sugar is in, blend on slow speed of mixer for 10 minutes to make a smooth icing.

title: jello spritz cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda.
In separate bowl cream butter. Gradually add sugar and dry jello.
Cream well after additions. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Gradually add flour.
Force through cookie press onto ungreased sheet.

title: easy fruit crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling and pineapple in ungreased rectangular pan, 13x9x2 inches.
Stir together dry cake mix and oleo in large bowl until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Bake 35-40 minutes or until light brown.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and beat 3 minutes or until well blended.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: egg souffle breakfast
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in a small amount of butter.
Cool.
Melt butter in baking dish.
In blender, mix eggs, cottage cheese and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with sauteed vegetables and sausage.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake for another 15 minutes.
If still runny in center, bake for an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Use a 12 x 8-inch pan for 8 large eggs, and a 13 x 9-inch pan for 12 large eggs.

title: fish baked over rice
directions: In 9x13 baking pan (spray with Pam) put rice (anywhere from 1 cup to 4 cups).
Put in water at twice the amount of rice.
Spread out rice after pouring the water in. Lay the fish on top. Put a few pats of butter around on it and season with your favorite flavors or just a little salt and pepper.
Wrap the top of the pan tight with foil.
Put the pan on a cookie sheet and put in the oven.
Bake at 350° F.
for about an hour, more or less, depending on how much rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: mashed potato fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Add mashed potatoes, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in sugar. Knead until smooth and press into buttered 8-inch square pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 1 1/4 pounds.

title: fruit cake
directions: Beat crackers until fine. Put marshmallows and milk in double boiler. Let melt. Slowly add cracker crumbs and other ingredients. Refrigerate. After it has set up, it may be sliced and served. Pack into round tube pan.

title: cheese dip
directions: Leave cheeses in bowl until very soft and creamy.
Mix together.
Add Worcestershire and mustard, then add the Port or sherry very slowly.
Put in a crock and refrigerate.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine whole corn, cream-style corn and eggs.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, mustard and onion.
Add milk and butter and mix. Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: steak pizzaiola ala bea
directions: Slice mushrooms, onion and garlic; chop tomatoes.
Trim meat and cut crosswise into very thin strips (3 x 1 1/2-inches).
Heat oil and butter in heavy skillet.
Brown meat on all sides, remove to platters.
Saute mushrooms for 3 to 5 minutes.
Place over meat.
Saute onion and garlic in skillet.
Add tomatoes.
Stir in parsley and oregano.
Season.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla and oats.
Mix well.
Spoon onto foil.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Score one side of steak, making shallow cuts in a crisscross pattern.
Place steak in a shallow dish or plastic bag.
Combine ingredients; pour over steak.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 3 days or at room temperature for up to 3 hours.
Grill over hot coals or broil 4 to 5 minutes each side.
Great served hot or cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix egg, milk and cheese together and set aside.
Crush the Ritz crackers.
Dip pork chops in egg mixture, then roll in crumbs, cover both sides well.
Put margarine in a pan, put the pan in a 350° preheated oven until margarine melts.
Add pork chops to pan in a single layer.
(Small, halved and peeled potatoes may be added at this time also.)
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chops and bake 30 minutes more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed on the package.
Drain any liquid.
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked swiss hamburger
directions: Mix hamburger, breadcrumbs, eggs and milk.
Pat out on cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Cover with waxed paper overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Remove all fat from beef. Cut into 2-inch thick strips.
Heat the butter in a Dutch oven and brown the beef, turning frequently to brown evenly.
Set the meat aside and cook the onions until they are transparent.
Set the onion aside.
Add the flour to the drippings and mix well.
Return the meat and onions to the Dutch oven and add bouillon cube, water and consomme.
Stir the mixture until it is smooth.
Add mustard, cover and cook very slowly for 1 hour or until the meat is tender.
Add the undrained mushrooms, Sauterne and sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: vege-chick-burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into patties.
Can be baked or fried in oil.

title: banana split salad
directions: Peel and slice bananas lengthwise.
Arrange with cut sides up on lettuce on 4 salad plates.
Mix pineapple and cottage cheese together and top bananas with spoonfuls of the mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherry.
(Top with teaspoon of mayonnaise, if desired.)

title: curry dip
directions: Blend and chill at least 4 hours.
Dip for vegetables or chips.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Spray a 9x13-inch casserole dish with non-stick vegetable spray.
In a bowl, mix together:
rice, soup, water, salt and pepper in bowl.
Pour into the prepared casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.

title: broccoli stuffed tomatoes
directions: Core each tomato and cut into five wedges, leaving them connected at the base, as for tomato blossoms.

title: cottage cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, cottage cheese, egg, oats, catsup, mustard, onion, salt and pepper. Mix well. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven. Remove and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven. Bake 10 minutes longer. Let sit about 5 minutes before cutting into squares.
Good cold in sandwiches.

title: chicken divan
directions: Partially cook broccoli.
Layer broccoli, chicken and butter. Combine mayonnaise, chicken soup, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over top; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, until golden brown, at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: apple pie(sugar free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together fruit, cinnamon, tapioca, oil, and apple juice concentrate; allow mixture to sit for 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into pie shell then use the other pie shell for top crust.
Bake 1 hour or until crust is golden.
Remove pie from oven and place on a wire rack to cool. Serve warm or cold.

title: jimmy cake
directions: *Shortening can be used in place of butter.
If the shortening is used, add 1 teaspoon salt.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Pour egg white over peanuts and mix until coated.
Add sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
Spread evenly onto an ungreased cookie sheet and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke and black olive marinara
directions: In a heavy 12-inch saute pan, cook onion in olive oil over moderate heat until lightly caramelized.
Add garlic and cook until fragrant.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered until desired consistency is reached, about 10 to 15 minutes.
If sauce becomes too thick, add water as needed.

title: the best rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and salt.
Boil unti rice is tender. Combine sugar and eggs, add to hot mixture slowly.
Combine evaporated milk and vanilla, add to mixture.
Cover over medium heat until thick, stirring frequently.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 cup bran and salt.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a covered dish.
Keep refrigerated; use as needed.
Lasts up to 2 weeks.
Add 1 cup dates, nuts or raisins, if desired.
Bake in greased muffin tins or muffin cups for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and set aside.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Spray baking dish; line bottom with bread.
Layer potatoes, sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You need enough milk and eggs to just cover the cheese.
I always use 2 more eggs when I use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown
meat
in
large pan, drain.
Add
all
remaining ingredients except tortillas,
mix	well.
Quarter	tortillas, use two 8 x 12-inch pans.
Pour
2 cups mixture in pans, layer tortillas and pour rest of	mixture over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Enough hot water to make into dough thick enough to shape into small loaves.
Break cracklins into small pieces.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 3/4 cup sifted powdered sugar. Cream well.
Add 2 tablespoons evaporated milk, vanilla and salt. Blend in flour.
If desired, chill.
Roll out half at a time on floured surface to 11 x 9-inch; trim sides.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares or 3 x 1 1/2 inch rectangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 16 minutes. Top each with 1/2 teaspoon filling, then 1/2 teaspoon icing.
Decorate with pecans.

title: hot tuna salad
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix together tuna, celery, 1 cup croutons, mayonnaise, almonds, onion, lemon juice and salt. Cover.
Microwave on Medium-high 9 to 11 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with cheese and remaining 1 cup croutons.
Microwave on Medium-high 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, chopped onion, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over cubed meat.
Stir to coat all pieces; marinate and refrigerate overnight, or leave at room temperature for 3 to 4 hours.
Alternate beef cubes and vegetables on skewers.
Cook over charcoal, basting with marinade.
Serve on rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked potato slices
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices, about 4 cups.
Mix soup, paprika and pepper.
Layer potatoes overlapping in rows in a greased 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover, bake 10 minutes more.
Very good with barbecue.

title: good ole coleslaw
directions: Shred the cabbage.
Mix with carrot and onion.
Whisk together mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper. Add to the vegetables and mix well.
Let sit in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, add caraway seed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas cherries
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, creaming well.
Add beaten egg yolks. Stir in flavoring, rinds, lemon juice and flour.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
While dough is chilling, chop walnuts and cut up candied cherries.
Beat egg whites with a fork until foamy.
Shape chilled dough into tiny balls.
Dip top of dough in beaten egg white, then in chopped walnuts.
Press a section of cherry into the middle. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: granny ocie's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, peanuts and salt on low heat until peanuts pop.
Take off heat and stir in soda.
Add vanilla. Spread into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda together and cut in shortening with 2 knives or a pastry blender.
Add cold buttermilk or sour milk.
Mix quickly, knead for a few seconds on lightly floured board.
Pat out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan close together for crust on top and bottom only, far apart if crust is desired on sides also. Bake at once in very hot oven (450°) for 12 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Drop by teaspoonful 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mix.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dori's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into loaf. Put into loaf pan and bake. Add potatoes and carrots around loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef & potato stew
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and tomatoes in stewer. Then add your stew meat, bouillon cube and potatoes. Fill stewer with enough water to cover potatoes. Add any seasonings you like. Cover and let simmer.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter; add onions, bell pepper and green onions.
Saute until soft. Add cream of celery soup and tomato sauce; stir. Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes. Add crawfish and simmer another 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: egg custard pie
