directions: Mix all the ingredients in a blender until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased glass pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This recipe makes its own pie shell.

title: puffed baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange fish in buttered baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and egg white.
Spread over fish and bake 15-20 minutes.
Easy.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix butter, soup, milk and mayonnaise together.
Bring to a boil.
Layer chopped cabbage, soup mixture, corn flakes and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Put in microwave for 10 minutes, then in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix the last 9 ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables. Cover tightly.
Let stand 12 hours, but should be stirred several times during this period for proper blending.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread. Cut into squares. Brown sausage and drain. Arrange half of bread in bottom of lightly greased 13 x 8 1/2 casserole dish. Top with cheese, sausage and remaining bread. Dissolve mustard in a little of milk. Beat eggs. Add milk, mustard, salt and pepper and pour mixture over layers. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Take out of refrigerator. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until firm. Serve with fresh fruit and sweet muffins.

title: yogurt gelatin delight(serves 6)
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Cover and refrigerate just until it begins to set.
Add yogurt and stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into a mold or dish.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir over medium heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Yields 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: edible clay
directions: Mix and knead well.
Shape to heart's content.
Then eat your project!

title: jim's "southern" cornbread
directions: A house should have a cookie jar

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook milk, sugar, cocoa and salt until sauce comes to a bubble and thickens slightly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Yummy over vanilla ice cream.

title: impossible green bean pie
directions: Cook
beans
as
directed
on package.
Drain.
Lightly grease pie
plate,
x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix beans, mushrooms, onion
and cheese
in
pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or one minute with hand beater. Pour
into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand
5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "celery bake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Combine butter and crumbs in bowls.
Mix well.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add chicken base, celery, onion and carrots to 4 cups water. Bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup water and broccoli and simmer another 5 minutes.

title: chinese fried rice(6 servings)
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet; toss in rice and heat until hot and golden.
Add scallions, salt and chicken; mix well.
Push rice to sides of pan and break 3 eggs into hollow.
Stir until lightly scrambled, then stir together with rice mixture.
Add soy sauce and cilantro; stir.
Serve.

title: company chicken
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over each piece of chicken.
Roll or shake chicken in corn flake crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole dish. Pour liquid whipping cream over chicken (almost covering it).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and eggs first, then add vanilla. Then mix in flour well.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to a rolling boil in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in flour. Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.

Remove from heat. Add eggs; beat until smooth. Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake until puffed and golden, 25 to 30 minutes. Cool thoroughly. Slice open and fill with Cream Puff Filling with powdered sugar.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle onions over top.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: settlers' beans
directions: Brown Hamburg.
Fry Bacon, drain and crumble.
Cut up Onion. When adding Beans, drain the Butter Beans and Kidney Beans.
Mix all together in a large bowl.
Bake in oven until bubbly or heat in pot on top of stove until bubbly.
Stir from time to time and be thankful to God all the time.
Serves 8 happy people.

title: strawberry frozen dessert
directions: Combine
milk, pie filling and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put
in
9-inch pan and freeze.
Take out one half hour before serving.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower well.
Cut into small pieces.
Cut onion into bite size pieces.
Mix in bacon pieces and salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar with mayonnaise, then pour over cauliflower mixture.
Do not stir.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Take out and toss gently.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar.
Mix until blended.
Blend in 1 egg.
In saucepan, combine water, margarine and chocolate; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add combined remaining sugar and flour; mix well.
Blend in remaining eggs, sour cream, soda and salt.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 jelly roll pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect; sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and cool.
Peel and cube potatoes.

title: bridesmaid's punch
directions: Mix juices; add ginger ale.
While still bubbly, add sherbet in large dollops.
Remove from freezer to let soften slightly!
Serves 20 to 25.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Use about 2 heaping teaspoons for a cup of tea.

title: cocretas
directions: Boil potato then mash.
(Do not overcook.)
Saute meat until golden brown.
Drain extra fat.
Combine meat and mashed potato. Form into balls or egg shape.
Coat with beaten egg and deep fry.

title: german potato salad
directions: Keep potatoes warm.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp, drain and reserve drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
To drippings in skillet, add flour and vinegar mix.
Cook and stir until slightly thick and bubbly.
After mix thickens, blend in sugar, salt, pepper, celery seed, onion, green pepper, pimientos, parsley and mustard.
Gently stir in warm sliced potatoes and bacon.
Add eggs.
Heat through.

title: soba(cold noodles)
directions: Heat all sauce ingredients and set aside to cool.
Cook Japanese soba noodles in boiling water until barely tender.
Drain and rinse well in cold water.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. When eaten, noodles are picked up with chopsticks and dipped in the sauce and slurped.
What we like is to mix the whole thing up and eat like pasta salad.

title: squash casserole
directions: Simmer squash in water for 6 minutes.
Drain squash.
Mix sour cream, butter, salt and paprika.
Gradually stir in cheese on low heat as it melts.
Add egg and chives.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: pineapple dessert cake
directions: Mix up cake mix according to package directions.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
It will be a thin layer; cool.
Blend the cream cheese with the milk.
Add vanilla pudding.
Mix 1 minute, then pour over cooled cake.
Spread crushed pineapple over cheese layer, then cover all with a large container of Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
May add some maraschino cherries for garnish.
Cool 8 to 10 hours or overnight.

title: vermicelli bake
directions: Cook vermicelli as directed; drain.
Brown hamburger; drain. Mix hamburger and spaghetti sauce; add vermicelli.
In a deep loaf pan, layer the spaghetti, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, spaghetti, Cheddar cheese and Romano cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Slice to serve.

title: beef fondue
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch cubes and salt and pepper.
Have sauces prepared.
Pour oil into metal fondue pot and heat it on the stove.
Place the pot on the chafing dish burner and begin.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Brown bacon and sprinkle in bottom of pie shell.
Add cheese. Mix eggs, cream and seasonings.
Pour over all.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until brown and puffy.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain fat and stir in cubed cheese. Add remaining ingredients, except bread; spread on bread.
Put in single layer on cookie sheets and freeze.
Microwave when you are ready to eat.

title: pineapple cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve 1/2 cup sugar in 1 cup hot water. Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water. Add sauce and mix well. Add all other ingredients and chill until well set.

title: bunny salad
directions: Make slits in pear and insert almonds for ears.
Make slits for nose and eyes and then insert cherry pieces.
Add marshmallow tail.
Surround by shredded lettuce.

title: summer salad
directions: Add all together and pour Italian dressing over top.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Peel and cube raw potatoes. Line a 9
x 13-inch pan with raw potatoes.
Cover with browned hamburger and
onion.
Pour soup and mixed vegetables together on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in casserole 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry jam bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Cream sugar, butter, vanilla and lemon juice.
Combine the two mixtures.
Add eggs, buttermilk and strawberry jam.
Mix well, finally adding nuts.
Pour in 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: bean hash
directions: Fry beef, bacon and onion until tender.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick and easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and remove from bone.
Mix in soup and sour cream.
Place mixture in a baking dish.
Top with herbed stuffing.
Dot top with butter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Soften oleo and cheese (do not melt).
Add flour, Rice Krispies and red pepper.
Make small balls and flatten with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° until slightly browned.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly (not done) and drain.
Cook rice in 2 cups water until done but not mushy.
Saute onion in margarine. Combine broccoli soup, milk, rice, onion, margarine, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour into two casserole dishes and sprinkle the remaining cheese on top.
(I usually use more cheese on top that it calls for, just cover the casserole.)
Makes two 2-quart casseroles.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in butter until soft.
Add chicken stock, basil, garlic and bay leaves.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and add the cheese a little at a time, whisking after each addition.
When all cheese has melted, add broccoli. Add the wine and check the flavor.

title: mindy's strawberry pie
directions: Prepare and bake a 9-inch pie crust and cool. Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in a saucepan, and boil until it becomes thick. Remove from heat and add strawberry jello. Cool mixture at least 5 minutes. Arrange the whole strawberries in the pie crust and pour glaze slowly over the strawberries. Refrigerate 3-4 hours or until firm.

title: strawberry jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Mix dry ingredients and add this to egg mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Add beaten egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix soup and tomatoes; set aside.
Add layer of tortillas, meat, beans and cheese in baking pan.
Add second layer.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Add cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake(serves many)
directions: Layer ingredients in a large punch bowl as follows:
1/2 cake (crumbled), 3 bananas (sliced), 1/2 of the pudding, 1/2 of the drained pineapple, 1 can strawberry pie filling, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and 1 cup pecans.

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix well and serve cold.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: colorful cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. In a large bowl, cream sugar, butter and eggs until light and fluffy. Mix in flour and cream of tartar. Stir in cereal. Put mixture into 1-inch balls and place 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool and eat.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/2 of cheese, oregano, garlic and pepper. Coat chicken with this mixture.
Put chicken in shallow pan and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Turn chicken and bake 20 more minutes.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese over top.
Bake 20 more minutes.
Makes a nice gravy that can be served over rice or noodles.

title: date cake
directions: Combine dates, soda and hot water, stir and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add flour, allspice, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in layers at 350° until done.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine until onions are transparent.
Add chicken broth, sherry and flour.
When slightly thickened, transfer to medium casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and both cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lime chiffon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and gelatin in saucepan.
In a bowl, mix egg yolks and water until smooth.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour into bowl.
Add lime peel, juice and coloring. Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Beat cream.
Fold in sugar.
Fold half of cream into lime mixture and fill pie.
Pipe rest of cream on pie and garnish with lime slices.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: spice molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: cocktail sausages in quick teriyaki sauce
directions: Use equal parts of jelly and barbecue sauce (approximately 1/2 cup of each per pound of meat).
Add meat to the heated sauce and heat through.
Serve with picks.

title: corn-cheese pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: jaeger schnitzel
directions: Take pork
cutlet,
slice
as thin as possible and beat with meat
hammer.
Dip into beaten eggs and bread crumbs; fry over medium
heat
until
golden brown.
After all cutlets are cooked, add
small
can
mushrooms to 2 cups gravy and pour over meat and serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain cooked vegetables and place in casserole.
Mix together cheese, onion and mayonnaise; pour over vegetables.
Crumble crackers and pour melted margarine over them.
Put mixture over cheese mixture in casserole dish.
Bake until crackers are golden brown at 350° about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pasta with shrimp and wine
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter and olive oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in wine, bouillon granules, basil, salt, pepper and red pepper (optional).
Bring to a boil gently, uncovered, for 12 to 15 minutes, until liquid is reduced by half.

title: cabbage-cheddar chowder
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, celery, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven until vegetables are tender; drain.
Stir in cabbage and water. Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is desired doneness, about 10 minutes.
Stir in milk, cheese, flour, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Garnish each serving with pimiento.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth, 1 minute.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until edges begin to brown.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread morsels evenly over top.
Cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling in oblong pan.
Dump pineapple on top. Add 2 cups cake mix.
Add 1/4 cup coconut.
Pour 1 stick margarine over mix.
Add remainder of cake mix on top, then place 1/4 cup coconut and nuts over mix.
Melt margarine.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: snack tidbits
directions: Mix cereals and pretzel sticks in a bowl.
Pour margarine and Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and salt (optional) over mixture.
Toss.
Spread on a large shallow baking pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
When cool, store in closed container.
Great snack for traveling.

title: thunder cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to box directions. Let cool. Poke holes in top of cake and pour Eagle Brand milk all over the cake. Let that soak in a few minutes. Do the same with the caramel topping. Let set for several hours. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with broken Heath bar pieces on top just before serving.

title: noodles florentine
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour, salt add milk, stirring constantly until thickened or instead of making white sauce, use either Knorr White Sauce Mix or McCormick White Sauce Mix. Add cheese to white sauce.
Place half drained noodles in greased 2 quart baking dish, layer ham, spinach, mushrooms and half the sauce.
Add remaining noodles and sauce.
Top with buttered breadcrumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden and bubbly in 350° oven.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out the centers, leaving a thick wall as a shell.

Cook meat in a large skillet until brown. Add onion, pine nuts, spices and butter. Stir and cook for 10 minutes. Stuff potatoes with mixture and arrange, skin side down, in a buttered baking pan. Cover either with canned tomatoes or water.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat together; add vanilla (beat until it changes color and is smooth).

title: microwave velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta and salsa, mixed together, in 1 1/2-quart microwaveable bowl on High 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.

title: homemade butter
directions: Beat ingredients together until smooth.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix well.
Putty must dry a bit before it is workable.
It may be necessary to add a bit more glue or starch; you will have to experiment.
Beware of contact with clothes and carpet.
If you use Elmer's school glue instead of regular white glue, the putty will not bounce or pick up pictures.
Store in an airtight container.
Recipe may not work well on a humid day.

title: coconut butter mochi
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add remaining wet ingredients, except coconut.
Pour into pan and sprinkle coconut on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-bake biscuit tortoni
directions: Line the muffin or custard cups with paper cupcake liners. Beat whipping cream and sugar in a chilled bowl until stiff.
Set aside 2 tablespoons macaroon crumbs.
Fold rest of crumbs, almond extract, cherries and almonds into whipped cream.
Spoon mixture into prepared cups and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm.

title: punch
directions: Mix 4 packages jello with 4 cups hot water to dissolve.
Add 4 cups cold water and mix.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice and sugar.
Mix well; then add 3 quarts cold water.
Stir.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix above ingredients, except ginger ale.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix croutons with melted butter.
Add hot water and sauerkraut.
Stir. Grease large casserole dish.
Begin layering with crouton mixture, sliced beef and Swiss cheese, ending with croutons on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and lay remaining cheese slices on top. Bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with Thousand Island dressing or mustard.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix
veggies,
mayonnaise
and cheese together.
Put in casserole dish and cover with crackers.
Pour melted butter on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the chips and flour, then mix in the nuts.
Roll by heaping teaspoonfuls into small balls. Bake about 10 minutes at 350° until lightly browned around the edges.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to brown sugar mixture with coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: pickles
directions: Mix lime in water (2 quarts). Wash and slice cucumbers. Put sliced cucumbers in lime mixture. Use enough water to cover cucumbers. Soak in lime mixture for 12 hours. After 12 hours wash and drain cucumbers. Mix all the other ingredients. Soak the drained cucumbers in the vinegar mixture for 12 hours. After the 12 hours cook cucumbers in vinegar mixture for 20 minutes from the time it starts to boil.
Pack in hot jars.

title: sweet and tangy pork
directions: Spread onion over bottom of 5 to 5 1/2-quart slow-cooker. Place the pork roast on top of the onion. Stir together the ketchup, chili sauce, 1/2 cup of the apple juice, the honey, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and red pepper flakes in a small bowl until well blended. Pour evenly over the pork roast. Cover the slow-cooker pot. Cook on high for 5 to 6 hours or on low for 10 to 11 hours, until the pork is very fork-tender. Remove the pork to a large platter; cover with aluminum foil to keep warm. Stir together the remaining 1/2 cup apple juice and the cornstarch in a small cup until well blended and smooth. Stir into the barbecue sauce in the slow-cooker. Cover the pot and cook on high for 15 minutes or until thickened. Slice the pork into thin slices. Spoon sauce over top. Serve with mashed potatoes or shredded on kaiser buns, if desired.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Chop pepper and onion; shred carrots.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Set in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: "toad in the hole"
directions: Cut round rump into dices and make batter. Beat egg very lightly; stir into milk with salt. Pour gradually over flour, beating until light and smooth. Butter a 2-quart baking dish; put in the meat. Season with butter, pepper and salt. Pour in the batter. Bake in a moderate oven for 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Marinate chestnuts overnight in soy sauce.
Wrap bacon around each chestnut and secure with toothpick.
Broil for 6 to 8 minutes and serve.

title: deep south barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Brush on chicken, pork or shortribs when grilling.
Or spoon over sliced, cooked beef brisket for a healthy, hearty barbecue sandwich.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cinnamon twirls
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Rub in shortening.
Beat egg and add milk.
Add to mixture only enough to moisten flour. Toss out on floured board and knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll into rectangular shape 1/4-inch thick, spreading with softened butter and sugar mixture.
(Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon to make cinnamon sugar.)
Roll up like jelly roll and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except potato chips.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can crumble potato chips on top before serving if desired.

title: twist rolls
directions: Use as many Twist Rolls from package of six as you need. Place the rolls on foil.
Slice butter and put on top of rolls. Sprinkle dill weed and garlic powder on top of butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: swedish one-crust apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full of sliced apples.
Sprinkle on 1 tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon.
In small bowl combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over apples.
Put in oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll cookie dough out on a cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake until done.
Let cool.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and non-dairy whipped topping together. Spread on cookie dough.
Mix strawberries with glaze.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: oven parmesan chips
directions: Slice potatoes thinly.
Mix all other ingredients together. Toss together with potatoes.
Spread in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender and beginning to brown.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Heat 1/2 of each margarine and shortening in each of two 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pans in 425° oven until melted.
Place chicken in pans, skin side down.
Stagger pans on oven racks.
Cook uncovered 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and rotate pans.
Cook uncovered 30 minutes longer.

title: quick chicken
directions: Slice chicken breasts in small pieces.
Place in casserole dish.
Place onion rings on top of chicken.
Pour salad dressing over onions and chicken.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes.

title: gem jam ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook.
Spoon over ribs or pork chops.

title: cinnamon punch
directions: Heat juice, candies and sugar until dissolved.
Chill.
Add ginger ale and crushed ice; mix to slushy consistency.
Makes 20 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onions and green peppers.
Add next 8 ingredients and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In baking dish arrange layers of half the noodles, half the cottage cheese, half the meat sauce, and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Cut large cucumbers in eighths lengthwise; let stand in ice water 8 hours or overnight.
Pack in hot sterilized jars; fill center of each jar with 2 pieces celery and 6 pickling onions.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix with 1/2 can of refried beans and 1/2 can of enchilada sauce.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture. Place in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with 1/2 can of enchilada sauce, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: giblet gravy(turkey or chicken)
directions: Return fat to pan over low heat.
Blend in 3 teaspoons flour, stirring with spoon until brown.
Pour in stock, giblets and eggs. Stir until boiling.
Add evaporated milk.
Simmer until thick and smooth.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: In a punch bowl, combine cider, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill; just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish as desired.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: fig strawberry jam
directions: Cover figs with water.
Cook until tender.
Drain and mash. Add sugar and jello.
Stir and boil 3 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: mary's cubed steaks
directions: Salt and pepper cubed steaks.
Put a little A.1. steak sauce on each cubed steak.
Get filling ready (chopped bread and flavoring). Put a handful of filling in each steak.
Roll the steak and put in ungreased Pyrex dish.
Mix mushroom soup with 1 or 1/2 can of milk. Spoon over steaks.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pound cake #1
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately, then add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Use tube pan.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat together the Jell-O and pineapple (undrained). Beat the cream cheese (softened). Slowly mix in Jell-O mixture.
Add the baby food and Cool Whip.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or large mold.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coke to boiling and pour over flour mixture; mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook celery and onions in a little chicken broth before mixing into mixture.
Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cracker crumbs and butter and return and bake another 10 minutes or until done.

title: frozen green salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in
2 cups boiling water; add pineapple (not drained) and food coloring.
Cool until syrupy.
Mix other ingredients and add to Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until set. Serves 16 to 20.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Pour melted butter and undiluted orange juice in wafers and sugar.
Mix again. Shape into balls (I allow the mixture to cool in the refrigerator first).
Roll in nuts or coconut if desired.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until center is done.

title: aunt lizzie's caramel filling
directions: Mix together.
Stir and cook until thick.
Beat and spread over cake.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form into meatballs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
When done, put meatballs in sauce and jelly and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pleasant party punch
directions: Thaw frozen juices.
Pour into punch bowl; add water.
Scoop out ice cream and place in punch bowl.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil for 4 to 5 minutes. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Serve with Cheddar cheese, chopped green onions and crushed tortilla chips on top. Freezes well.

title: apple tortillas
directions: Grease or spray a baking dish.
Spoon pie filling onto tortillas and roll as you would enchiladas and place in baking dish side by side so they touch.
Combine water, butter/margarine, sugar and cinnamon in a pan and bring to a low boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over tortillas in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil for first 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Blue Bell Homemade Vanilla.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a large dish or pan. Chill until set.
Add the bananas, marshmallows and pineapple.

title: irish stew
directions: Take 1 1/2 pounds of mutton or lamb in season and cut into small pieces.
Slice 3/4 pound of potatoes and 3/4 pound of onions.
Put into a saucepan.
Cover with cold water; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to boil slowly.
Simmer for 2 hours or until the meat is tender.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Steam clams in 6 cups water.
Remove from shells and chop clams.
Save shells.
Save broth.
In large bowl, put clams, 1 cup clam broth (water), carrot, onion, garlic, red pepper, margarine, bread crumbs, basil and Italian seasoning.
If too dry, add more broth.
Put in shells.
Top with bacon, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Enjoy.

title: low-fat strawberry pie
directions: In 1 (10-inch) pie pan, crush crackers.
Mix yogurt and applesauce.
Press into pie pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Cool. Wash and hull strawberries and slice or leave whole. Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until mixture is thick and glossy, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and simmer 5 minutes. When mixture is clear, add Jell-O and lemon juice. Stir and cool.
Add strawberries and pour over crust.

title: pepperoni en croute
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On an ungreased cookie sheet, roll crescent dough in one piece and pinch perforations together.
Brush pepperoni with egg yolk and then roll in flour.
Place on dough and roll up, covering completely.
Tuck ends neatly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice and serve immediately.

title: soda cracker cake
directions: Crush crackers, mix crumbs, sugar and nuts together.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Mix with cracker mix.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Cool completely.
When cool, cover with a layer of Cool Whip, a layer of pineapple and a layer of coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly together; add egg (well beaten), strawberry extract, milk, sifted flour with powder and salt.
Beat with a wooden spoon for 3 minutes.
Turn into a large, well-greased mold.
Cover and steam steadily for 3 hours. Turn out and serve with crushed strawberries and whipped cream. Other fruits may be used in place of strawberries.

title: banana chiffon pie
directions: Make a large pan of ice water.
Set empty mixing bowl in water. Place 1/3 cup tap water in a small pan.
Pour 2 teaspoons of unflavored gelatin over to soften.
In mixing bowl, measure 2/3 cup powdered milk.
Add equal, extract and 1/3 cup ice water.
Stir. Plug in electric hand mixer.
Bring gelatin and water to a boil. While mixing at high speed, add gelatin mix to milk.
Mix and continue to whip until like whipped cream.
In pie tin, layer cream; add banana and top with rest of cream.
This is a once a week fruit and all the milk for one day.
Eat any time.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Place artichokes in bottom of casserole pan.
Place spinach over artichokes.
Spread cream cheese mixture over all.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top of cheese and bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil. Add eggs and milk, then dry ingredients. Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: wiener bean casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, put milk, mayonnaise, flour, salt, mustard, pepper and onion in blender or whip together.
Pour over rest of ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in a small amount of stiffly beaten cream.
Fold cream cheese into remainder of whipped cream.
Mix other ingredients.
Put into heart shaped mold.
Freeze until firm. Let stand 3 minutes to thaw.
Serve on lettuce.

title: grandma's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Blend soups, rice and milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Lay chicken over top.
Brush with butter; season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add beaten egg yolks. Combine nuts and fruits with some of the flour and stir until coated.
Add flour, a little at a time, to creamed mixture. Add extract and grape juice. Add fruit and nuts; fold in.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in. Bake in well-greased tube pan at 250° for 4 hours or until done.

title: brown sugar chewies
directions: In large mixing bowl, melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well until dough is soft.
Add nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until sides bake away from side of pan. Insert toothpick in center to check for doneness.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese-vegetable soup
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onion in margarine in 4-quart Dutch oven until celery and onion are transparent, about 10 minutes. Stir in baking mix, paprika, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat; stir in half and half and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with popped corn, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Brown hamburger; place in pot.
Cover with water.
Add bouillon.
Add Veg-All (drained) and stewed tomatoes.
Add orzo. Simmer for 20 minutes and serve.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough and separate into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press the diagonal perforations to seal. Place several pepperoni slices on each rectangle to taste. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of cheese on the pepperoni.
Starting at the short side, tightly roll each rectangle.
Pinch dough to seal. Slice each roll into 4 equal slices, pinching dough together on one side of each slice to seal.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with pizza sauce, if desired.

title: williamsburg eggnog
directions: Dip ice cream with a small scoop and freeze in a jelly roll pan.
Beat eggs until frothy in a 3-quart bowl.
Beat in sugar, ginger, cinnamon and cloves until blended.
Stir in orange and lemon juices.
Cover and chill if using later.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Crumble cake and set aside.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar, then add Cool Whip to this mixture.
In a large bowl, put a layer of crumbled cake, Cool Whip mixture and then 1 can of cherry pie filling.
Repeat layers.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: eclair pie
directions: Make pudding by directions.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip together.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer crackers and pudding.
After second layer, put a layer of crackers.
Top with frosting.

title: mana pua
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Mix salt and sugar together; add to yeast.
Add flour.
Mix with hands; knead and put into bowl. Cover with cloth and leave 2 hours.
Punch down; cover and let rise again, 30 minutes.
Oil hands and make 2 inch balls.
Flatten in palms of hands and fill with about 1 Tbsp. filling.
Pull dough over filling and close by pinching and twisting edges together. Place on 3 X 3 inch piece wax paper; pinched edge down.
Grease rack of steamer.
Pull small cloth on top cover of steamer to collect water.
Steam for 40 minutes or longer.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Add bananas.
Mix well. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: no bake mini cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottoms of each of 12 paper or foil lined muffin cups with spoon or bottom of glass.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on dinner sized plate.
Put in fridge until firm.
Mix crabmeat and sauce.
Spread over cream cheese.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: italian beef
directions: Put in pan with 3 cups water and 1 can tomato sauce.
Bring to boil with the Italian seasoning dressing mix and the bay leaf. Pour over meat.
Cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on high.

title: homemade instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together and keep in tightly closed jar.
To serve, add 3 teaspoons of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dump into large bowl and mix very well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Divide into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Blend well ingredients, except Lawry's seasoned pepper. Sprinkle well with Lawry's seasoned pepper.
Use as dip or topping for fancy sandwiches.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain grease. In a separate pot, boil curly noodles until tender and drain. Mix together the noodles, hamburger and onions and add spaghetti sauce. Mix well. Pour into a baking dish and top with pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve with bread and a salad.

title: wild rice with sausage
directions: Saute the bulk sausage or link sausages, removing the casing. Drain on paper towels and break the meat into small pieces.
Saute the mushrooms and onions in the sausage drippings.
Add the cooked sausage.
Wash the rice thoroughly.
Cook in boiling salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Mix the flour with cream until very smooth.
Add the chicken broth and cook in a saucepan until thickened.
Season with oregano, thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper. Combine with rice, sausage and vegetables.
Toss together lightly.
Add pepper seasoning.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Put rice on platter.
Makes 12 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour. Mix well.
Stir in melted oleo or butter and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, water and strawberries.
Add pineapple and marshmallows; let it congeal.
Top with Dream Whip mixed with cream cheese.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Good dip to use with carrots, celery and cauliflower.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients together until they spin like a web thread 4 to 6 inches long when dripped from spoon.
Add peanuts.
Continue cooking until syrup begins to turn gold, stirring frequently.
Peanuts will begin to pop and smell parched. Quickly stir in oleo and baking soda.
Pour onto well buttered 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
When it begins to set, mark into thirds. When hard, put out on table by turning over flat and tapping bottom of pan.
Break into pieces.

title: beans a la keeno
directions: Wash beans (do not soak), add onion, salt, meat, tomatoes, A.1. and tomato sauce.
Fill pot with water to cover beans.
Boil for 1 hour.
Add tomato soup and potatoes and cook slowly, adding water to keep from sticking (stir often).
Cook about 2 to 3 hours until done.

title: golden punch
directions: Boil sugar with 1 cup water; add remaining water and chill. Combine all ingredients in listed order, adding ginger ale and soda just before serving.
Serves 60.

title: easy baked beans
directions: In ovenproof dish, mix all ingredients.
Place bacon strips on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season pork chops as desired and brown under broiler.
Heat soup in broiler.
Place an onion slice on top of each chop.
Pour soup over top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
The extra soup will make an excellent gravy for rice.

title: zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4 inch slices into frying pan.
Cut up tomato into 1 inch cubes.
Saute in butter until soft.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Simmer covered for 1 minute.
Serve.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add pecans.
Mix remaining ingredients and toss with pecans.
Bake at 250° for an hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: moist sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add the other ingredients in order listed.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Dip the bottom of a glass in granulated sugar and press cookies slightly.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes (do not overbake).
Cool on wire racks.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix milk, water, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour in shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg. Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 25 to 30 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill.
Refrigerate any left over.

title: pineapple coconut dump cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with butter Pam.
Layer in pineapple, coconut and cake mix.
Pour melted oleo over it.
Put nuts on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil hard for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add the 1/2 cup peanut butter and the 3 cups quick oatmeal.
Blend.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Beat together shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Mix apple butter in well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp floridian
directions: Add salt and pepper to flour in paper bag as you would to prepare chicken for frying or place flour in flat pan or dish with salt and pepper and dredge shrimp in mixture.
Melt butter in large shallow pan on top of stove.
Simmer garlic buds, chopped, in butter.
Do not allow butter to brown.
Remove garlic or leave it in, as you like.
Add shrimp in single layer to butter.
Cook, just until shrimp turn yellow.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Cook slowly 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and sherry.
Ladle this sauce over shrimp.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Stir well.
Sauce and flour will thicken.
Serves to 4. Menu might include corn on the cob, tiny green peas, tossed salad, rolls, coffee and non-rich dessert.

title: breakfast potatoes
directions: Cook bacon over medium heat until crisp in 10-inch omelet pan. Remove bacon; drain and set aside.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon bacon fat.
Add potatoes to pan.
Cover; cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cook, covered, until eggs are nearly set.
Arrange tomato slices on top; sprinkle with cheese and reserved bacon (crumbled).
Cover pan; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with soup, cheese, sour cream and hash browns.
Place into a 12 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or longer, if needed to brown.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Beat eggs and milk; add chilies and cheese.
Pour into ungreased 8-inch square Pyrex dish and bake until set (like custard) at 350°.
Cool and cut into 1 inch squares.

title: firehouse chicken
directions: Combine dressing, soup and preserves.
Coat breast with mixture and marinate 4 hours in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprayed with cooking spray (Pam does well).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered; then 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: perfect cobbler
directions: Mix together peaches, sugar, lemon peel, lemon juice and almond extract and arrange in a greased 8 1/2-inch or 9-inch round baking dish.
Place peaches mixture in 400° oven.

title: cinnamon nut pudding
directions: Cream
sugar and butter.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk to shortening and sugar.
Place this in a greased pan.
Bring brown sugar,
water and butter to a boil. Pour this over first mixture and sprinkle nuts over all.
Bake 45 minutes (oblong pan) at 350°.
May be served warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, "Adams Best" vanilla, Adams butter flavoring and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add.
Mix well.
Then add German chocolate that has been softened in warm oven or in double boiler.
Blend together well.
Bake in 9-inch stem pan or 10-inch Bundt pan, that has been well-greased and dusted with flour, about 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove cake from pan while still hot and place under a tight fitting cake cover and leave covered until cold.

title: oyster pie
directions: Butter casserole generously.
Layer cracker crumbs on bottom. Alternate onion, oysters, crackers and butter.
Beat egg, milk and liquid from oysters.
Add lemon pepper and dill seed.
Pour over pie.
If needed, add milk to fill to top.
Grate frozen butter over top.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes, until set.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine the beef carrots, celery, onions, sugar, potatoes, tapioca and tomato juice.
Place the beef mixture in a covered greased casserole and bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk and beat.
Add sour cream.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Use remainder of Cool Whip on top.

title: orange crispies
directions: Blend ingredients well; spread generously on about 30 slices of bread.
After spreading, cut each slice into thirds and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
(Two cookie sheets could take a little longer.) Don't cut off crusts.

title: peachy trifle
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat at low speed
of electric mixer 2 minutes or until blended and thick. Add cream cheese and yogurt. Beat well.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes.

Line bottom of a 2-quart straight sided glass bowl or trifle with 2 cups cake cubes. Spoon 1 1/2 cups pudding mix over cake. Arrange 2/3 cup peaches, 2/3 cups bananas and 1/2 cup kiwi fruit over pudding.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, ending with kiwi. Cover and chill 3 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: fish chowder
directions: Put bacon in 3-quart pan and cook until crisp.
Cook onion until transparent.
Stir in soup,
milk and seasonings.
Cook until liquid simmers.
Add fish cubes.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: You will need an 8-inch pie pan.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook fryer with onion in enough water to have at least 1 quart of broth until fryer is done.
Cool and debone; break meat into pieces.
Cook noodles.
Mix chicken, noodles, broth, soups, sour cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 10 1/2 x 14 1/2-inch baking dish or pan.
Cover with bread cubes, then melt margarine and spoon over top of bread layer.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: christmas cookie kringle
directions: Through a strainer the hard-boiled eggs you force, using the back of a spoon.
Then combine with the raw egg yolk.
Work in the sugar, butter and shortening, then the flour, cinnamon, vanilla and all of the rind.
Form into a ball.
Chill.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Use doughnut cutter or biscuit cutter and place on a cookie sheet.
Paint each cookie with unbeaten egg white. Sprinkle with pistachios.
Bake at 350° 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into walnut size balls and chill 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: crispy crunch cookies
directions: Mash bananas to make 1 cup.
Cream sugars and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in mashed bananas, egg and vanilla until blended.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat into banana mixture.
Beat in granola and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful three inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to complete cooling.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Put raisins and water in pan.
Heat slowly, about 10 minutes, to plump raisins.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Boil slowly, about 15 minutes, until thickened.
Makes 2 cups of sauce.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add chicken and mushroom soup. Add chilies. In casserole, place tortillas in bottom. Pour meat mixture over top of cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Spread frosting over cake. Yield:
16 servings.

title: candied bacon
directions: Mix brown sugar and dry mustard.
Place bacon on wire rack on cookie sheet.
Coat with sugar mixture.
Bake at 300° until brown and crisp.
Drain and cool.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix as any fruit cake.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan that is lined with brown paper and greased.
Bake at 250° to 275° for about 2 hours.
Place pan of water on top rack of oven over cake.

title: congealed salad
directions: In small saucepan, stir Jell-O and undrained pineapple together and bring to
a boil.
Set aside until room temperature. In very large mixing bowl, fold buttermilk into Cool Whip.
Stir the Jell-O and pineapple mixture into buttermilk and Cool Whip mixture.
Stir until well mixed and color is uniform.
Pour into large oblong Pyrex dish or mold (fits great in the Tupperware ring mold).
Makes a delicious holiday salad!!

title: watermelon cooler
directions: Blend sherbet and ginger ale.
Pour over blueberries and watermelon in 4 tall glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order, beginning with lettuce, in a glass bowl. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix sour cream and soup; add chicken.
Melt margarine, add crackers and poppy seed.
Layer cracker mixture and chicken mixture in casserole, beginning and ending with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and spicy chicken wings
directions: Mix together salad dressing mix, honey and orange juice.
Set aside 1/4 cup for dipping.
Marinate 24 pieces of chicken wings (first and second joints) at least 1 hour, then broil 5 minutes on each side until chicken is cooked and glazed.
Serve with dipping sauce.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all the ingredients for the dressing in medium-size bowl. Prepare vegetables and place in large bowl.
Pour dressing over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable batter
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water.
Stir in ginger.
Dip vegetables in batter; drain and fry in deep oil.
Use chunks of broccoli, cauliflower, zucchini, celery and mushrooms.
Drain on paper towels.

title: banana pudding
directions: Place sliced bananas and wafers in layers in dish.
Mix instant pudding and milk; add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Pour mixture over bananas and wafers.
Chill overnight.

title: rice pie
directions: Soak 1 cup rice in 2 cups of milk for about 2 hours.
Add 2 more cups of milk.
Cook over low heat for about 20 minutes.
When fully cooked, add 2 beaten eggs and sugar.
Add remaining milk (1 cup) and cinnamon.
Put in a few drops of whiskey to taste.
Add to mixture and stir.
Put in pie crust (do not cover with crust). Makes 2 pies.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Mix in vanilla.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoon onto foil lined cookie sheets.
Place in 350° oven.
Turn oven off immediately.
Leave overnight or equivalent.
Makes 2 cookie sheets or about 3 dozen.

title: cabbage rolls #1
directions: Remove cabbage leaves and cover with boiling water till they become limp.
Drain.
Combine ground beef, 1/2 chopped onion, salt and pepper and rice.
Mix well.
Shape meat in oblong roll and roll in cabbage leaf using a toothpick to hold together.
Place stuffed leaves in roaster and cover with water.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
In fry pan, saute remaining onion and shortening. Add vinegar and tomato soup.
When cabbage rolls are done, drain and reserve 1 cup liquid.
Add heated soup ingredients to cabbage rolls with the reserved liquid.
Thicken with the cornstarch mixture.
Return to oven for about 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place margarine in large baking pan and heat until margarine is melted. Set aside. Beat together milk, eggs, flour, sugar, salt and pepper until well mixed. Add corn, green pepper and pimentos. Place mixture in baking pan. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour. Pudding is done when center appears jellied upon gently shaking pan.

title: nachos(cheese topped tortilla chips)
directions: Cut each tortilla into 6 pie shape pieces. Heat oil and deep-fry tortillas until crisp. Drain and cool. Place chips on a cookie sheet. Spread each with beans, then sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 325° until cheese melts. Top each with
a jalapeno slice. Serve hot. Omit beans, if desired. Makes 6 servings. Preparation time: 0:45.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add onion, egg and milk.
Stir until just mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil in a deep pan.
Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: lemon bars
directions: Press into a 9x13 pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Add all ingredients; stir constantly over a medium heat. Boil till it forms a hard ball in cool water.
Place pot in water in sink and stir or beat until stiff.
Pour in a greased pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup (do not add milk).
Pour this over chicken.
Bake in oven 1/2 hour at 350° covered with lid, then remove lid last 10 minutes to brown.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Remove water from sour cream by letting it stand awhile.
Add Blue cheese to sour cream and mash until cheese is dissolved.
Add juice of 1 onion.
Add parsley and salt.
Store in refrigerator in covered jar.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar.
Beat milk and egg yolks, then add to dry mixture.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Add meringue, if desired.

title: corn-n-bean casserole
directions: Drain and then mix together.
Place in a casserole dish.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients together. Blend next 6 ingredients together.
Gradually add flour to all of these ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and pecans. Drop "golf ball" size cookies 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.

title: sunday dinner steaks
directions: Dredge steaks in flour and pepper.
Brown lightly on both sides in hot oil.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over top.
Cover with canned mushrooms and liquid.
Layer on sliced onions.
Pour gravy which has been mixed with 1 gravy can of water over top.
Do not stir.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: marge's chili bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add cheese and melt. Then add in chili with beans; mix well.
Serve dip hot with chips.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Grate or chop vegetables.
Then in a saucepan, combine vinegar, water and sugar.
Heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil and sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over cabbage mixture. Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Can be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: deep dark chocolate cake(from hershey's cocoa)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour either 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Combine dry ingredients. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans, 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out onto cooling rack.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Remove crust from loaf of unsliced bread.
Grate into fine crumbs (2 or more cups).
Spread out on pan to dry overnight.
(May substitute this amount of cornflake crumbs.)
Mix crumbs with cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip each piece of chicken into melted butter (1/4 pound in all), then into crumb mixture.
Be sure each piece is well coated.
Arrange pieces without overlapping in a shallow roasting pan.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake 1 hour or until fork-tender, at 350°. Do not turn pieces.

title: southern zucchini
directions: Peel and dice zucchini; boil 10 minutes or until tender.
Mix onion, carrot, soup and sour cream; add drained zucchini to mixture.
Make stuffing with butter and water.
Line casserole with stuffing mix; add zucchini mixture and put the rest of the stuffing mixture over the top.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes covered and 40 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream your margarine and sugars together, then add the eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Add the chips, Kisses and nuts last.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: skinless fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and wash.
Soak overnight or during the day in salty water.
Dip chicken in chicken breader and fry slowly, about 40 minutes.
Then remove part of oil and bake about 20 or 30 minutes at 350°.
Ovens may vary.

title: microwave beef stew
directions: Place meat into a 4-quart glass casserole.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and boiling water; cover with an all-glass lid.
Cook in microwave oven 10 minutes on High.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion to liquid in casserole.
Stir.
Cook, covered, in microwave for 60 to 75 minutes at Simmer or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Be sure meat and veggies are covered with liquid during cooking.
Add hot water if needed; let stand, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Thicken liquid for gravy, if desired.

title: simply elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips (best when frozen).
Brown in oil. Add onions. Saute until tender.
Blend remaining ingredients, except rice, and add to steak.
Add 1 can of mushrooms, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summer tasting barbecue spareribs anytime
directions: Pour honey and barbecue into two separate bowls.
Dip spareribs into honey bowl first, thoroughly coating rib.
Next, dip rib into barbecue sauce, coating to preference.
Layer ribs in crock-pot and cook on low setting for six hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, bananas and oil together; sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add pineapple and fold in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: dressing for cabbage slaw
directions: Slice onion thinly and shred cabbage.
Pour 7/8 cup sugar over vegetables.
Heat the 2 tablespoons sugar, celery seed, vinegar, salt, salad oil and mustard and pour over cabbage while hot.
Let set 4 hours or more before eating.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour in both cans of peaches.
Top with cake mix.
Put slices of butter all over the top of cake mix about every 3 inches.
Put in 350° oven until light brown on top.

title: pork cutlets
directions: Cut tenderloins crosswise into 1 inch rounds.
Pound the pieces gently between sheets of plastic wrap until they are thin cutlets.
Dredge each piece in flour then water, then eggs, then bread crumbs.
Refrigerate for 1 hour to keep the breading on better when frying.
Heat the oil in a skillet over moderate heat. Add butter.
Fry the cutlets a few at a time until they are golden brown.
Put a rack in the bottom of a roasting pan, then crumple aluminum foil on top of the rack.
Place the cutlets on top of the foil.
Add 1 cup water to the bottom of the pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Let cherries drain.
Freeze cherries.
Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Flatten to about 1/2 dollar. Place frozen cherries in center; wrap mixture completely around. Chill overnight.
Boil chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip in mixture with cherries.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook hamburger meat and sausage and drain.
Add rice, onion, salt and pepper, celery salt, thyme and oregano and cook until mixed.
Put cabbage in hot water to wilt.
Cut leaves from cabbage head.
Add meat mixture, then roll this mixture up in the cabbage leaf.
Stick a toothpick through to secure the leaf.
Pour tomato sauce over the cabbage rolls and cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20 cabbage rolls.

title: sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Cut tenderloin into strips; brown in hot oil.
Add water, bouillon and salt.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: peaches 'n cream punch(a great non-alcoholic punch)
directions: In a blender container, combine undrained peach slices, pineapple juice, egg, ice cubes, lemon juice and vanilla.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Stir in cream.
Slowly pour in carbonated water (stir in an up and down motion).
Pour into chilled glasses. Makes about 8 servings.

title: just good gumbo
directions: To prepare roux,
mix flour and oil thoroughly in heavy pot. Place
over
medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent sticking. When roux turns dark brown, turn off heat, 30 to 60 minutes.

title: my spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all other ingredients, except spaghetti noodles, adjusting more or less oregano, garlic salt and salt and pepper to your taste.
Simmer 2 hours.
Use less water if cooking time is shorter.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange half of the potatoes in a layer.
Pour 1/2 of the sauce on top; repeat.
Sprinkle paprika.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes. Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer, until tender.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix.
Add cocoa and vanilla; mix well.
Gradually add flour, then coconut and walnuts. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
While still hot, drop by spoonfuls 1 jar of marshmallow cream.
Cool completely.
Mix melted butter, cocoa and sweetened condensed milk.
Spread on top of cake.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Stuff 12 jars with whole or sliced cucumbers, a clove of garlic and a pinch of alum and dill weed (large sprig).
Boil together water, vinegar and salt.
Pour into
packed jars and put hot lids on top to seal.
Make sure jars seal.
If they did not seal, put in refrigerator; use these first.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll thin, cut in diamond shape (4 x 4-inches or 5 x 5-inches).
Cut a 1-inch slit below one point and slip the opposite point through it.
Fry in deep fat at 370° for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out rounded loaf of bread; fill with dip and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; strip skin off.
Save 3 cups of broth.
Melt margarine in bottom of a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 of the stuffing in bowl and mix slightly.
Break chicken in bite-size pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Begin by layering the chicken, then soup mixture.
Continue layering until all ingredients are in bowl.
Place the remainder of the stuffing over the top.
Pour the broth (3 cups) slowly over the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a mixing bowl, combine 1/3 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, beat egg yolks, add milk, lemon juice, butter and lemon peel. Add to the dry ingredients and mix well. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff peaks form, fold into lemon mixture. Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2 qt baking dish. Place in a large baking pan, add 1-inch of hot water to large pan. Bake uncovered for 45-50 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm or chilled.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Put all vegetables in a bowl.
Pour Italian dressing over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
This keeps well for several days.

title: fresh strawberry and rhubarb lemonade
directions: Wash rhubarb and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Add 2 cups water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain and add sugar.
Stir until dissolved; cool.
Crush strawberries; strain and add lemon juice and water.
Serve in tall glasses over ice.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham, potato, cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Cut ham steak into cubes, peel and thinly slice potatoes. Place 1/2 of the potatoes in casserole dish layered.
Add 1/2 cubed ham, 1/2 package broccoli and 5 slices of cheese.
Repeat all the steps. (You will have 2 layers of each.) Place in microwave for 45 minutes or until potatoes are soft (or pierce with fork).

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually.
Work flour into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Form into small balls.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll into powdered sugar.

title: eggnog-cranberry salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pudding mix, lemon Jell-O and 2 cups water; cook, stirring until mixture boils.
Stir in lemon juice; chill until partially set.
Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; beat in cranberry sauce.
Fold in celery and nuts. Chill until partially set.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, onion and green pepper. Add drained beans. Chill until time to serve. Immediately before serving, add Fritos, cheese and dressing. Makes a large bowl.

title: granny's potato salad(a childhood memory)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Peel zucchini and remove seeds from center.
Cut into chunks and place in a large kettle.
Add sugar and pineapple juice. Bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack into clean jars for canning.
Place filled jars in a canner of boiling water and process for 20 minutes.
Use in recipes calling for pineapple.

title: my mother's sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Beat well and set aside.

title: puppy chow(for people)
directions: Pour Crispix into largest Tupperware bowl there is.
In a pan melt the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over the Crispix.
Stir cereal until coated with the melted mess.
Pour the box of powdered sugar over cereal.
Put lid on bowl, seal and shake thoroughly so all mixture is coated with sugar.
Pour out on cookie sheet, separating into bite-sized pieces.
Allow to dry completely.
Wash Tupperware bowl and store mixture in it after dry.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: trio baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onion in bacon grease.
Drain limas and pintos.
In ovenproof dish, add pork and beans.
Cut cheese into 1-inch cubes.
Add other ingredients.
Cover; bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spinach salad with dressing
directions: Place salad ingredients in a bowl.
Mix salad dressing; toss together.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: super orange rolls
directions: Mix the sugar and orange rind in a bowl.
Dip each biscuit in butter, then coat in sugar mixture.
Stand on edge in 2 rows in a bread pan.
Sprinkle any leftover sugar mixture on top and some butter.
Bake at 375° for approximately 35 minutes, until golden brown on top.
Turn out, upside down.
Let cool a few minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix thoroughly and mold.
Can freeze for extended time.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook beans according to directions.
Blend mushroom soup and milk.
Drain cooked beans and add to soup mixture.
Reserve 1/3 cup onions for toppings; add remaining onions to green bean mixture.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle reserved onions on top.
Bake 25 minutes or until hot and lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: crab delight party dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 2 hours.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the dressing.
Butter baking dish and sprinkle with herb dressing, heavily.
Add squash mixture and top with more dressing.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned, about 45 minutes.

title: sunday sticky buns
directions: Break dough into pieces and place in an 8 or 9-inch pan (the night before).
Mix remaining ingredients, pour over the dough. Let rise overnight in the refrigerator (can let rise for 2 hours out of the refrigerator if in a hurry).
Remove from the refrigerator, bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
(They are done if brownish.)
Cool for a few minutes and turn out onto a plate (be careful, the caramel topping is quite hot!).

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put in grinder and blend the cranberries, apple, lemon and orange.
Add cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, walnuts and sugar. Mix well and chill overnight.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Thaw
spinach;	place
on
paper towels and press until barely moist.
Combine
all
other ingredients and stir well. Cover
and chill for several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Stir in raisins and caraway seed.
With fork, blend in buttermilk and melted butter until evenly moist.
Turn into casserole and cut an X or T on top.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
It is advisable to check before time is up.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: whipped cream layer cake(blotkake)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and butter.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add sugar.
Combine flour and egg mixtures and beat well. Knead; divide into 9 portions.
Roll each portion into a plate sized piece.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 cakes.

title: bonnie's holly wreath holiday salad
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water with mixer or eggbeater until frothy.
Fold in sour cream and mix well.
Add pineapple and cherries.
Pour into a 1 1/2 or 2-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: easy chocolate mousse
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Pour into dessert glasses and chill several hours before serving.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onion.
Alternate in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Put both cans of soup (undiluted) on top of potatoes.
Dip pork chops in milk, then bread crumbs.
Place on top of potatoes. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Take foil off.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: erica's after school burritos
directions: Warm tortillas, then put in fillings and roll up.
This is a great after school snack to hold you over until supper.

title: spinach cheese casserole
directions: Mix together, turn into 1-quart greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan, if desired.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add sugar to yams, then add oleo, beaten eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In a large bowl, mix sausage, garlic, hamburger, V-8 juice, rice and oats.
Stuff the peppers with the mix.
Place peppers in a casserole dish.
Pour can of tomatoes over the peppers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve the peppers with 2 cups of cooked rice.

title: diet german chocolate cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Then mix cream cheese and sugar well.
Add Cool Whip, pecans and Hershey bars. Makes a lot of icing.
Put a lot between layers.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Sift cake flour three times.
Alternate eggs and flour with butter mixture, beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Cook in well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: surprise package
directions: Mix meat with salt and pepper.
Form into a ball and press flat.
Peel and slice vegetables.
Place meat on foil, then layer vegetables on top of meat.
Top with margarine and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold foil and seal ends to make an airtight package.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May add mushrooms or different vegetables, but things like shrimp cook too quickly and will overcook.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Brown and drain celery and onion. Mix together with rest of ingredients.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Chinese noodles on top.
Bake uncovered for another 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread, biscuits and bread and mix well.
Saute onions and celery.
Mix bread mixture, onions, celery, sugar, parsley, salt, pepper and sage (optional) well.
Add deboned chicken and cooled chicken broth and soup.
If need more chicken broth, can use Swanson's chicken broth.
Cream of chicken soup gives it a richer taste.
Make mixture a little juicy.
Add chopped or finely crumbled boiled eggs last.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hint for newspaper article preservation
directions: Mix and set overnight.
Pour in a glass 9 x 13-inch dish. Soak paper clipping 2 hours.
Remove and lay on paper towels. Let dry.
Will keep 200 years.

title: susie pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Put in floured tube pan. Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: nut roll
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, raisins and nut meats.
Blend Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add to crumb mixture and knead well. Form into roll.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown (saute) ground beef; add onion and garlic.
Drain off all grease.
Add taco seasoning mix, tomatoes, Ro-Tel, tomato sauce and soup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Layer:
Meat sauce, flour tortillas, sour cream, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake at 325° until hot and cheese melts.

title: lou kridelbaugh's famous layer cake
directions: Put cake in hand.
Locate Lou.
Slowly, quietly sneak up on Lou.
Smash cake in Lou's face.
Make sure the entire event is documented on film.
After smashing cake in Lou's face, run like the devil, all the while relishing your victory.
(Warning:
Be prepared to receive same.)

title: chewy cocoa brownies
directions: Melt oleo; add cocoa, then add all other ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Nuts may be added.
Serves 30.

title: vidalia onion casserole or pie
directions: Saute onions
in half of oleo.	Melt rest and pour over Ritz. Beat
eggs	and combine all ingredients;
pour into pie crust or greased
casserole	dish.
Bake
about 30 minutes at 350°.	(Crush Ritz in tube before you open.)

title: "cheese ball"
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Alternate with milk and flour, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: carol channing's "hello dolly cookies"
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour graham cracker crumbs over oleo and spread.
Pour coconut over and spread.
Pour nuts over and spread.
Pour chocolate chips over and spread.
Pour the Eagle Brand condensed milk over the whole works and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
