Let cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into balls.
Put a marshmallow in the center of each ball.
Roll each potato ball in shredded coconut and place in a buttered pan.
Cook 5 minutes or until coconut browns.

title: lasagna(microwave)
directions: Brown meat in an extra large Pyrex mixing bowl for 3 to 4 minutes.
Cover
with
paper
towel
while	cooking.
Drain liquid.
Be
sure
all
pink is gone.
In same bowl add sauce, meat
and
water.
Layer 1/3 meat sauce, layer of noodles (the extra
water will absorb into noodles), 1/2 cottage cheese and egg mixed
in	cheese.
Sprinkle 1/2 Parmesan cheese.	Repeat with enough left for top.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Gather by mid-morning.
Contrary to belief, vegetable appears first (behind blossom) so pick only blossoms that directly join the stem.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Spread with CHS sauce.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast according to package directions.
In a large bowl, stir flour, salt and yeast mixture until blended.
Cover bowl with waxed paper; let rise 5 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes or until thickened.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine and blend well the mayonnaise, onion, pickle, olives, celery, mustard and tuna fish.
Add to macaroni; mix well and chill.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Dip tomatoes quickly in hot water, then in cold.
Remove skin and core.
Scoop out inside of tomato and save pulp.
Season tomatoes with salt and pepper and turn upside-down to drain. Brown onions in butter.
Add flour to thicken.
Add half and half and stir until thick.
Add cheese and bread crumbs.
Add part of tomato pulp into mixture.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire and nutmeg.
Stuff tomatoes and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: trash can pickles
directions: Make brine with salt and water in a 4 or 5 gallon plastic can with lid.
The brine should be salty enough to float an egg.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the oil, for 3 minutes, using the lowest speed of the mixer or by hand until well mixed.
Then slowly add the oil as you mix for another 3 minutes, still using the lowest speed or stirring by hand.

title: dutch slaw
directions: Combine a 3-pound head cabbage, one chopped green pepper and one chopped medium onion.
Cover with 1 cup sugar.
With knife, poke holes through cabbage.
Bring cooking oil, vinegar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and stir.

title: zesty chicken pasta salad
directions: Cut chicken in strips. Combine all other ingredients; mix well. Mix chicken and pasta last. Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie no. 2
directions: Melt
butter
and cocoa.
Mix all ingredients together. Fills two pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water in large container.
Reconstitute frozen orange juice as directed on can.
Combine with sugar syrup, lemon juice, pineapple juice and bananas.
Freeze until firm. Thaw for 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Mash until slushy.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions until just tender, frozen vegetables only.
If using canned vegetables, use straight from can.
Place vegetables in a greased casserole dish. Next, mix onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise in a bowl and spread over vegetables.
Melt margarine; mix with crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Combine all ingredients and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour bread starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add the sugar and potato flakes; mix well. Let stand in glass or crockery out of refrigerator for 1 day. Place in refrigerator for 3 days.
On third day, take out and feed with 3 teaspoons potato flakes, 1 cup warm water and 3/4 cup sugar. Let stand out of refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours. You are now ready to bake bread.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients until sticky. Shape into 2 or 3 rolls. Wrap tightly in foil and refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; drain and cool.
Combine next 4 ingredients; stir until blended.
Add to macaroni, stirring well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: sausage and pepper
directions: Poke sausage with fork.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Saute peppers and onions; add sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
When sausage is done, cut into bite size.
Drain grease from pan.
Add sausage, peppers, onions and sauce.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes.

title: turkey hash
directions: Cook turkey and onion in about 1 1/2 cups water.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
When potatoes are done, add bread. Cook 5 minutes longer, then serve.

title: french country soup
directions: While bringing water to a boil, chop the vegetables.
Saute garlic 1 minute; add chopped vegetables.
Saute lightly.
Drop noodles in boiling water while vegetables saute.
Pour kidney beans with juice into boiling noodles.
Add vegetables to stock. Chop parsley and basil together and add to soup stock.
Add tomatoes (if canned, include juice).
Add cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured pan.

title: green beans(for those who don't like veggies)
directions: Cook bacon in microwave first. Crumble bacon. Combine all ingredients and cook until all flavors mingle together, about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, margarine, white sugar and brown sugar. Add remaining ingredients except the preserves; mix.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Put preserves on top and cover filling with more batter.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown; drain.
Prepare seasoning package as directed.
Add refried beans.
Layer chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with beef mixture.
Pour melted cheese over beef.
Layer lettuce, cheese and tomatoes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with creamed cheese frosting.

title: raspberry punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine 7-Up, pineapple juice and Kool-Aid. Add sherbet and ice cream; stir.
Ready to serve.
You can change flavors by changing sherbets and Kool-Aids.

title: noodle and spinach casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute 1 stick butter, onion, red and green bell pepper, minced garlic, juice of lemon, crushed red pepper, oregano, parsley flakes and 2 cans of minced clams with their juice.
(Add crushed bacon, if desired.)
Add bread crumbs to mixture and mix very well.
Place mixture into an ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp and broccoli
directions: Saute shrimp in oil and garlic and salt.
Then add broccoli, wine and a little water.
Cook covered approximately 5 minutes, add cornstarch (mix starch with water until the right consistency).
Broccoli should be crunchy.
Serve immediately.

title: fried fish
directions: Soak fish in V-8 juice 1 to 2 hours.
Bread fillets (using paper bag with dry ingredients).
Shake.
Then fry in hot oil. (You may use some Cajun seasoning to rub fish before coating.)

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, ending with salt.
Place half the mixture in a greased and floured tube pan.
Mix nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Spread over cake mixture.
Add remaining cake batter.

title: kahlua caramel french toast
directions: Combine the butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until the butter melts, stirring to blend well.
Stir in 1 tablespoon Kahlua.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange the banana slices in the dish.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soup, water and cheese in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually fold in 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix egg yolks and water and beat until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until thick and lemon colored.
Add lemon extract.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg white mixture.
Fold in flour mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Turn out on towel dusted with confectioners sugar.
Trim off hard edges and spread jelly on cake.
Roll up lengthwise.
Wrap in towel or wax paper until ready to slice.

title: graham cracker pecan roll
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Spread on wax paper; roll and put in icebox and serve with whipped cream.

title: homemade mincemeat for pies
directions: Cook beef in water to cover; save broth.
Cool and grind meat like hamburger.
Peel apples, core and slice or dice fine, or can be cooked and stirred like sauce.
Mix meat, raisins, currants, sugar, cherries, apples, vinegar, spices and part of meat broth. Can always add more if too thick.
Cook for several hours until thickened and not too runny.
Add cider or wine (optional) or more broth.

title: baked mullet
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt in a roasting
pan.
Pour sauce made with remaining ingredients over fish.
Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes, turning and basting a few times.

title: vegetable corn bread
directions: Saute vegetables in medium sized cast-iron skillet that has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine egg whites, milk and oil/applesauce and stir into dry ingredients.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Spread in skillet.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: tuna spread for crackers
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Top with additional cocktail sauce, if desired.
Chill until ready to serve.
Great served with assorted crackers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, flour and apples.
Put in bottom of baking dish and dot with butter.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and egg until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples and bake at 350° until apples are tender.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar and baking powder.
Beat 2 minutes until glossy. Fold in crushed Ritz crackers, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased aluminum pie pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: willow's magic rings
directions: Remove top from can of pineapple. Drain juice into small saucepan, leaving pineapple in can.
Heat juice until simmering. Dissolve Jell-O over pineapple slices in can.
Chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: pineapple filling for cake
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks and margarine in saucepan. Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, or until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add pineapple that has been drained.
Cool and spread.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: english plum pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Fill 4 (1 pound) coffee tins 1/2 full.
Cap the cans and steam for 5 to 6 hours.
These should be made at least 2 months before using and kept in the refrigerator during that time.
If using a pressure cooker, steam only 3 1/2 hours at 10 pounds pressure.
Serve pudding hot with this sauce.

title: old-fashioned sour cream dressing and cabbage
directions: Beat all ingredients, except cabbage, together until stiff. Mix thoroughly with the cabbage.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: For Pecan or Cashew Brittle:
Omit peanuts and add 1 cup pecan halves or dry-roasted cashews.

title: green beans oregano
directions: Cook beans until barely done in unsalted water. Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Save 2 slices bacon for garnish. Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors (very important).
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6. Recipe is easily doubled.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cover bottom and sides of 9 x 9-inch baking pan with crescent roll dough.
Cook sausage in skillet until brown and crumbly; drain well.
Layer sausage and cheese in prepared pan.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour over layers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie meat loaf
directions: Mix in large bowl first 5 ingredients.
Add ground meat and next 9 ingredients.
Combine well but do not over mix.
Transfer mix to an oiled Dutch oven or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Allow to stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Leftovers make great sandwiches.

title: breakfast in a cup(low-fat)
directions: Combine rice, 1/2 cup cheese, chilies, pimientos, milk, eggs, cumin, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Divide mixture evenly into 12 muffin cups coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until set.

title: yellow party cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy (about 8 to 10 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer), scraping bowl frequently.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed about 2 minutes or until mixture is light and fluffy. Scrape the bowl frequently.

title: spinach, bacon and mushroom salad
directions: In medium salad bowl, combine spinach, mushrooms and bacon; toss.
Top with croutons and eggs; season with pepper.
Pour salad dressing over all.

title: quick raisin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light, then add milk, salt and raisins and mix well.
Add melted shortening.
Sift all-purpose flour.
Measure, then sift again with baking powder and stir into first mixture.
Fill greased and floured bread pans half full of mixture and let stand 20 minutes.
Bake for 60 minutes in moderate oven (350°).

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a bowl. Stir in unbeaten egg whites and almond extract.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are browned.
Remove from sheets at once.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: baked bananas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place bananas in 9-inch square baking dish.
Heat orange juice, rum and preserves until full boil and preserves are melted.
Pour over bananas.
Sprinkle with coconut. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until heated through.
Serve over ice cream or pound cake.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add taco seasoning and tomato juice. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chicken pastel
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce and lemon juice.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Place chicken in a saucepan, add water, salt and pepper. Simmer until tender and almost all the pepper has evaporated. Set aside.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Brown chicken pieces.
Drop in slices of chorizo de bilbao, Vienna sausage.
Pour broth; cover and cook until half done.
Mix in green onions, carrots, potatoes and mushrooms.
Cook everything together.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons flour, if necessary.
Transfer cooked mixture to a Pyrex dish, garnish with slices of hard-cooked eggs.
Cover Pyrex dish with pie crust.
Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In a large glass or crockery bowl, alternately layer the sliced cucumbers, onion and green pepper. Mix the vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed until the sugar dissolves. Pour over the layered vegetables. Cover and refrigerate. Chill several hours before serving. Store up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator in a glass jar.

title: cracker barrel potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add soup and desired amount diced onion and pepper. Stir in grated cheese and add to potatoes. Put this mixture into a greased glass 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: You will need muffin cups.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: Rinse shrimp.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in shrimp. Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley, lemon rind and Tabasco sauce.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and cover the bottom.
Set aside.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on greased cookie sheet; do not pull apart.
Pat together at seams.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes. Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled pastry.
Top with vegetables of choice.
Sprinkle with 1 cup gourmet shredded Cheddar cheese.
Tastes best when made a day ahead.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add applesauce.
Mix well. Stir in sifted dry ingredients into first mixture, alternating with water.
Blend raisins and nuts into batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix together and cook to soft ball stage.
Beat until mixture starts to thicken.
Drop on wax paper or pour on wax paper into pie pans.
Makes 5 patties in pie pans.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef and onion in 1/2 cup water until brown.
Add ketchup, mustard and soups and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring last 3 ingredients to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and marinate at least 5 to 6 hours.

title: slow cooker barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Trim excess fat from beef. Cut beef into 4 pieces. Place beef in 4 to 5-quart slow cooker. Mix remaining ingredients, except buns; pour over beef. Cover and cook on low heat setting 7 to 8 hours or until beef is tender. Remove beef on low heat setting 20 to 30 minutes longer or until beef is hot. Fill buns with beef mixture.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions and cool.
Mix together pudding and cream cheese.
Spread over cake.
Spread drained pineapple over this mixture.
Next, smooth whipped topping and then coconut.
Add nuts, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sloppy tom
directions: Saute onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in turkey, catsup, chili sauce, water and mustard. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir occasionally. Spoon into buns.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Enjoy.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Place broccoli or asparagus in the bottom of a loaf pan (10 x 6 x 2-inches).
Add the turkey, then soup with milk added.
Add cheese and top with crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruited pork salad
directions: In jar with tight-fitting lid, shake together first six ingredients.
Set aside.
Spray large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray and heat to medium heat.
Stir-fry pork slices 3 to 4 minutes until done.
Arrange lettuce on individual plates.
Top with fruit and pork.
Spoon dressing
over salads. Serves 4.
Nutrient information per serving:
calories 267; cholesterol 67 mg.; fat 8.9 g.; protein 27 mg.; sodium 81 mg.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix to make an ordinary cake.
Put in cupcake pans. Combine cream cheese, sugar and egg; beat well.
Add chocolate chips.
Put by teaspoonful onto top of each cupcake.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with seven minute frosting.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine 15 caramel candies, each cut into 4 pieces.
Add 1/3 cup of flour.
Add 3 cups of chopped apples (1/2-inch cubes), 2/3 cup caramel ice cream topping and 2 teaspoons of lemon juice; mix well.
Pour the mixture into a frozen pie shell.
Bake at 375° on a preheated baking sheet for 1 hour.
Store at room temperature.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onions and peppers in large saucepan.
Add ground beef, tomatoes, mushrooms, garlic and seasonings.
Allow to cook about 1 hour.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Put 1/4 sauce in bottom of lasagna pan.
Cover with 1/3 noodles.
Use 1/2 Ricotta cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Continue in order, ending on top with noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle of Parmesan.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian chicken breast
directions: Put the chicken breasts in a glass dish.
Pour the Italian dressing over the chicken breasts.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Then turn the chicken over.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 more minutes or until done.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Bring squash, sugar and lemon juice to boil.
Simmer just to a boil for 30 minutes.
Take off heat and add a box of any flavor Jell-O.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Immediately put into jelly jars.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato and cucumber.
Arrange tuna mixture, tomato and cucumber on serving plates.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple filling for cake
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and butter together until pineapple is clear.
Add cornstarch and enough cold water to mix.
Boil until thick.

title: guacamole
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and beat with an electric mixer until thoroughly blended.
Great with tortilla chips or on baked potatoes.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread each ham slice with a thin layer of mustard and/or mayonnaise.
Roll one slice of ham around each cheese stick.
Cut in half crosswise; set aside.
Divide dough into four rectangles along perforations.
Press diagonal perforations to seal.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each into an 8-inch square.
Cut each into four 4-inch squares.
Place one ham and cheese roll diagonally across one corner.
Fold dough over ham; roll to center of square.
Fold sides in and continue rolling to opposite corner.
Dip top of each roll in melted butter or margarine.
Press seam-side down on an ungresaed baking sheet and sprinkle with seed.* Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 16.

title: vegetable souffle(grontsagsfromage, danish)
directions: We sometimes use frozen mixed vegetables.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together, kneading by hands until consistency as desired.
Add coloring and flavoring. Pinch off small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Press into candy molds.
Remove any excess and remold onto waxed paper. Makes about 60 mints.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and meat until pinkness disappears and onion is soft.
Turn off heat. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Combine sour cream and eggs.
Pour over top of pie and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° until crust is brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: dago dish
directions: Put cabbage, partially cooked sausage and water in large pot. Add one 15 ounce can of diced tomatoes and tomato paste. Simmer, covered, until cabbage is tender. No salt and pepper necessary.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add to beef the garlic, salt, sugar, pepper, chili powder, cumin and flour.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes;
cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute.
Add and cream brown sugar and white sugar with melted butter.
Add sifted flour, pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Pour in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir pudding mix, pineapple with juice, marshmallows and nuts in large bowl until well blended. Gently stir in whipped topping. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve. Garnish with additional whipped topping and sliced strawberries, if desired.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on potato chips. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, peanut butter and syrup; stir in nuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Combine butter and sugar until smooth.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in flavorings, pecans and chocolate chips.
Spoon into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: In large baking dish, slice potatoes.
Add onions.
Put shredded cabbage on top of onions.
Crumble corned beef on top of cabbage.
Add a little water to mushroom soup and pour over top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered, until potatoes are cooked.

title: yeast bread
directions: Scald milk; cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in a small amount of the water.
Add yeast and remaining water to the cooled milk. Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Add flour and mix thoroughly. Knead dough on a floured board.
Place dough in a greased bowl. Cover and allow to rise in a warm place until dough will retain impression of a finger.
Punch gas from dough by plunging fist into center of dough.
Fold over edges and turn upside-down. Cover and let rise in warm place until dough is half again as its original side.
Remove to floured board and flatten out.
Divide into 4 pieces; mold into balls.
Allow to stand closely covered for 15 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in greased bread pans and cover.
Allow to stand until dough fills the pan and the center is well above top of pan.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: cookie pie crust(excellent for strawberry pie)
directions: Mix together and flatten into pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, watching closely.
Brown lightly.
Cool.

title: zeppolis
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs for 3 minutes.
Add Ricotta; beat for another 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Drop batter from a teaspoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown. Sprinkle with sugar.
Serve warm or cold.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute seasoning in butter.
Add rice and water.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add corn and soup.
Add parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Top with grated cheese.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, salt and cocoa. Cream butter and sugar. Add flour mixture. Mix in soda and buttermilk. Mix in egg and vanilla (don't beat egg). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine whole tomatoes, tomato paste, onion, sugar, garlic powder and spices.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: karo coconut pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and Karo until light and fluffy.
Add coconut and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes or until the pie will not shake in middle.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices together.
Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in oil and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients slowly and mix well. Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Cool completely in pan.
Turn onto cake plate and icing.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in ungreased pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: basil biscuits(low calorie)
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in 2 cup liquid measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk and set aside.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until pea size.
Add buttermilk mixture, basil and tomatoes, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened. (Dough will be sticky and lumpy.)
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.
Yield:
1 dozen.
Great with soups.

title: "kitty's" peas and rice
directions: Cook peas or beans in coconut milk or cream.
When cooked, add scallions, thyme, pepper and salt.
Let come to a boil, add rice and reduce heat to medium for rice to steam.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix green beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese, onions and salt.
Place in greased casserole.
Mix melted margarine, crushed crackers and almonds.
Spread on top of casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Best if made the night before serving and put in refrigerator before baking.
Excellent for freezing; add topping just before baking.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook egg noodles as directed; drain and set aside.
In an ovenproof baking dish, melt the cheese.
Add chicken, soup, broccoli and egg noodles; mix thoroughly.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add wate slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks, butter, lemon rind and juice and pinch of salt.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made with egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 20 minutes.

title: sauce for sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Heat to boiling, pour
over meatballs.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: brown paper bag apple pie
directions: You will need 1 brown paper bag (grocery bag).

title: easy pot roast
directions: Brown roast in large roasting pan on top of stove.
Add water. Fill so bottom of pan and roast is immersed in 1/2-inch water. Clean potatoes.
(Do not remove skins.) Place potatoes in bottom of pan and on top of roast.
Clean and peel carrots.
Cut carrots in half lengthwise and add to top of roast and potatoes.
Cover. Bake in 350° oven for 4 hours.
Delicious even without seasonings. Serves 6 or more.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch baking pan with vegetable oil spray.
In a medium bowl, whisk together sour cream, skim milk, "butter" granules, cornstarch and pepper.
Set aside.

title: tea cakes
directions: Note: Dates may be added to mix.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Cook turkey.
Size of pot will determine cooking time.
A 20 to 22-quart pot with 3 gallons of oil will handle a 12 pound turkey and take about 4 minutes per pound; 25 pound turkey, 3 minutes per pound.
Oil should be 380°.
To spice outside of bird, use salt, pepper, seasoning salt, etc.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: mints
directions: Press in desired candy molds.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: To make starter:
Mix ingredients in a glass jar or container. Cover loosely and let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Put in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.
On the fourth day, feed it with 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons potato flakes and 1 cup warm water.
Stir and keep at room temperature 24 hours.
One cup of starter is used to make the bread.
Store remaining starter in the refrigerator until the next feeding.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Open and roll out crescent rolls in pizza pan.
Cook, crumble and drain sausage and sprinkle on crust.
Sprinkle hash browns on sausage.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and salt and pepper to taste together and pour over pizza.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: savory sausage rice
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet; pour off excess fat.
Add green pepper, onion and 1 cup celery; saute.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in large saucepan.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Add sausage mixture and salt.
Stir well.
Pour into a greased baking dish, 12 x 8 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle remaining celery over top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 20 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Drain fruit juice into cup.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add fruits to jello and set.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.
(Good with pork.)

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Press flat with a fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: lazy daisy meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, seasonings, crumbs, 1/2 cup water and onion. Form into balls; roll in flour and brown in hot fat.
Mix soup, 1 soup can water and coloring; pour over browned meatballs.
(If you want more gravy, which is yummy over mashed potatoes, use 2 cans of soup and 2 cans of water.)
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate brittle
directions: Use cookie sheet.
Fit saltines on bottom of cookie sheet. Break to fit entire sheet.
Melt the butter with the sugar on stove. Stir well.
Pour over crackers evenly. Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Take out and sprinkle bag of chocolate chips evenly over crackers.
Put back in oven for 2 minutes. Remove.
Use spatula to spread melted chips evenly over crackers. Refrigerate to harden, then break up into pieces and serve.

title: fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; cook and stir 5 minutes longer. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until smooth. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Cook and cut into squares. Makes 24.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat and add to crock-pot. Saute onions and garlic about 2 minutes. Add onion, garlic and all other ingredients to pot and cook on low for 5 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add milk and eggs, blend well. Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: maple oatmeal bread
directions: Combine sugar, salt, boiling water, coffee, oats, shortening, and syrup. Let cool to lukewarm. Add to the above mixture the yeast dissolved in the 1/4 cup of lukewarm water. Blend in the egg gradually; add flour and mix until smooth. Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Place in greased bowl, cover with dish towel and let rise until double in size. Knead a little and shape into two loaves. Let rise and bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Combine pudding and milk and spread on top.
Top with 4 ounces Cool Whip.

title: hot puppies
directions: Clean peppers; leave whole.
Stuff hot dog pieces into hot pepper.
Pack tightly into wide mouth quart jars.
Make mixture of remainder of ingredients.
Pour over peppers 1/2 to 1-inch from top of jar.
Cold pack 5 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie(from stephenson's apple orchard restaurant)
directions: Combine peaches with sugar, flour and spices.
Put in unbaked crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lattice crust.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In a food processor with a metal blade, combine all ingredients and blend up to 30 seconds or in the blender.
Stir after 15 seconds.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: punch
directions: *3 c. chilled champagne may be used.

title: quick apple loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Gradually blend in well-beaten eggs, apples and juice. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together and stir into the apple mixture. Add nuts and pour into well-greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 55-65 minutes.

title: hardtack
directions: Heat sugar, water, Karo syrup and vinegar to hard crack stage. Remove from heat.
Add oil and coloring.

title: pineapple filling
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Slowly stir in pineapple juice, then add remaining ingredients.
Over low heat, heat mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, until smooth and thickened.
Cool.
Fills a 2-layer cake.

title: lasagna primavera
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon margarine until tender. Remove from skillet.
Saute carrots, onion and garlic in 3 tablespoons margarine until carrots are tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix together 2 cups Mozzarella cheese with cottage cheese, spinach (thawed and drained well) and Parmesan cheese.

title: ethel's salad
directions: Boil the 7 cups liquid.
Pour over Jell-O.
Add vinegar and salt.
Let stand until partially cool and set.
Then add fruits and vegetables.
Mold and chill.
Serves 40 people.

title: barbecue meatballs or frankfurters
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into 16 balls and fry in small amount of fat until brown, then combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat in skillet.
Cover and cook slowly 10 minutes turning meatballs occasionally.

title: crusty breadsticks
directions: In small bowl, soften yeast in water for 5 minutes.
Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives until very fine.
Add softened yeast; mix until dough is formed.
Cover; let dough rest in bowl for 20 minutes.
Cut off pieces slightly smaller than golf balls.
Roll 10 to 12 inches long.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Brush with wash made of egg white combined with water. Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake in a 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: squash puffs
directions: Cook squash till tender and drain. Mash and measure 1 cup. Combine dry ingredients and mix well. Add squash, egg, and onion; stir. Drop by level teaspoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until golden brown, turning once. Yields 2 dozen.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; mix well.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla; mix well.
Press 2/3 of dough into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread with jam and sprinkle remainder of dough over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares. Makes 36 squares.

title: chocolate pinwheels
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and milk and beat well.
Add flour, small amount at a time, mixing well after each addition. Divide dough into 2 parts.
To one part, add chocolate and blend. Roll each on floured wax paper into rectangular shape 1/8-inch thick.
Lay plain sheet over chocolate sheet.
Remove wax paper. Roll like jelly roll.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: brown rice supreme
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes covered.
Can be baked in microwave also.

title: farm house cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream shortening in mixer bowl at medium speed about 1 minute. Gradually add sugar; mix at medium speed 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Scrape down bowl.
Combine slightly beaten eggs and water; add gradually to creamed mixture.
Blend thoroughly about 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients; mix only until ingredients are combined about 1 minute.
Add chocolate chips; mix on low speed about 1 minute or until evenly distributed.
Drop by tablespoons in rows 4 by 6 on ungreased pan. Using a convection oven, bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned on high fan.
Open vent.
Loosen cookies from pans while still warm.

title: italian fettucine alfredo
directions: While noodles are cooking, beat egg yolks lightly with fork, then add the milk, sour cream, melted butter and Parmesan cheese. Cook on low heat, then add noodles.
Add additional Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into baked 10-inch pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir in dry ingredients. Chill dough. Form into small balls. Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until light brown, but soft.

title: pigs in a blanket casserole
directions: Grease lightly a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put in thick layer of cabbage.
Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Spoon mixture over cabbage along with rice.
Heat soup and water just to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients.
Sprinkle cabbage over top and sprinkle cheese over top of cabbage.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place dried beef in bottom of 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Wrap chicken with bacon and place on top of dried beef. Mix together soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered, and 1 hour, uncovered.

title: raisin pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add milk alternately with flour to Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flavorings.
Fold well drained raisins into batter. Spoon batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, or until done when tested.

title: marinated barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover; marinate 8 hours or overnight in the refrigerator, turning occasionally.

title: baked scallops
directions: Melt butter and add spices to crackers.
In 4 individual bowls, place 1/2 pound scallops per bowl, topped with cracker stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: heavenly divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and corn syrup together until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cup of water.
Beat egg whites and salt at high speed 3 minutes.
Pour syrup mixture slowly into beaten egg whites while beating at high speed.
Continue beating until mixture forms a peak when beater is raised.
Pour on buttered platter or drop on waxed paper.

title: spinach or broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix all other ingredients and fold in vegetables.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into pan.
Sugar lightly.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Work together with fork.
Spread over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: gavin's favorite apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, flour, cinnamon, apples (grated finely) and pecans.
Pour in greased pan and bake on 350 degrees for 1 hour or until brown.

title: zesty black-eyed peas
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 3 slices bacon and 3 chopped onions.
Sprinkle these on top; cover and chill at least 8 hours.

title: buttermilk persimmon pudding
directions: Add sugar to pulp, then add beaten eggs, stirring well.
Then add soda to buttermilk.
Stir until foaming ceases.
Add buttermilk to first mixture and stir well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into persimmon mixture and beat well.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and cream.
Put butter into pan to melt, pour into batter, except enough to grease pan.
Beat well and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan in slow oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: hot dog hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut each hot dog into 3 pieces.
Slit across each and both ways (+).
Fry hot dogs until ends flower out.
Put apricot preserves and mustard into fondue pot.
Add hot dogs and serve.

title: jeanne bolar's frittata
directions: Drain juice from jar of artichoke hearts.
In a small pan, add onions and garlic; brown.
Add following to a bowl:
eggs (beaten) and chopped parsley; stuff in pan.
Mix altogether; put in buttered 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: basic chicken soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion, celery and carrots until tender. Add remaining ingredients and heat until hot.

title: banana, date and nut bread
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs, then add mashed bananas.
Add flour and baking soda; mix, then add dates and nuts.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg; set aside.
In separate bowl, mix baking soda and buttermilk thoroughly.
To this mixture, add flour, bananas, pecans and vanilla.
Blend in the creamed butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: praline cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring well. Add flour and salt, stirring well. Stir in pecans. Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: deep dish biscuit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in tomato paste, mushrooms, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer all these ingredients.
Press refrigerated country biscuits into greased 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Spoon mixture into crust. Slice 1 tomato and arrange it atop this pie.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: mother's green tomato mincemeat
directions: Note:
Any leftover jelly or fruit juice, boiled cider, etc. may also be added.

title: souped-up meat loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Spray a glass or metal loaf pan (standard size) with nonstick cooking spray. Next in a medium bowl, mix all the ingredients together, except the ketchup. Mix until well blended. Shape into a loaf and place in the loaf pan. Spread the ketchup on the top. Bake in the preheated oven for approximately 50 to 55 minutes. Check for doneness.

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients to dish, saving sliced peaches for last.
Do not stir.
Top mixture with sliced peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Put packages of tapioca and vanilla pudding into a pan and place on stove.
Add 3 cups hot water.
(Do not add milk called for on package.)
Cook on heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add package of orange Jell-O (dry) and stir until dissolved.
Set aside and let cool.
Drain all canned fruit.
After mixture has cooled, add mandarin oranges, pineapple and fruit cocktail and blend together.
Fold in 1 large container Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: deluxe hash browns
directions: Empty partially thawed hash browns in large bowl.
Combine balance of ingredients and mix into the potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley or paprika for color.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. (Very good with ham dinner.)

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add meat and brown lightly, stirring frequently. Stir in mushrooms, rice, onion and soy sauce.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Add and stir in egg.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and add eggs.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients.
Add molasses and ice water and alternate with flour. Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon and sprinkle a little sugar on top and add a nut or raisins, too, if so desired.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and fettuccine
directions: In saucepot, prepare fettuccine as label directs; drain. Return fettuccine to saucepan; keep warm.
Cut each chicken breast in half.
In a small bowl, beat egg slightly.
On wax paper, mix 1/4 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Dip chicken pieces into egg, then into flour mixture to coat evenly.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Follow instructions on cake mix, omitting water and replacing with drained orange juice.
Add oranges to batter, bake and cool.

title: frosted orange drink
directions: Put in blender all ingredients.
Fill the rest up with ice cubes.
Blend until ice is crushed and drink is frosty.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing according to directions.
Cook green beans (canned green beans can also be used).
Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package stuffing, then chicken and green beans.
Place second package of stuffing on top.
Mix soup and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Good with leftover turkey also.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Put all in blender.
Chill and serve.

title: holiday sausage swirls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into rectangles.
Spread with a thin layer of uncooked sausage.
Top each rectangle with 2 tablespoons sharp Cheddar cheese.
Roll (from short end).
Chill until firm.
Thinly slice each roll. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 80 swirls.

title: french bread
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast onto 1/4 cup very warm water.
Stir and let stand until it bubbles.
Pour boiling water over shortening, salt and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add 3/4 cup cold water and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and gradually beat in enough flour to form stiff dough.

title: litely sweeten bread pudding
directions: Soak the bread with milk and pineapple with juice.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Add liquid sweetener, eggs and vanilla to mixture.
Mix well, then add all dry ingredients and mix again well.
Spray an 8-inch square pan with nonstick spray. Pour mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until inserted cake tester comes out clean when testing.

title: magic biscuits
directions: Mix well and
drop
by	tablespoon
on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 18 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Cool. Beat eggs until light.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Add chocolate mixture.
Mix thoroughly and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top should be crusty and pie should shake like custard.
Top with ice cream to serve.

title: root beer float
directions: Into a large chilled glass (not plastic), add root beer and ice cream, 2 scoops, then add toppings if desired.

title: sis. anderson's chocolate poundcake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix rest of dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: oriental snack mix
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine pretzels, raisins, chow mein noodles and peanuts.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and paraffin.
When melted, quickly pour over pretzel mixture and stir.
Spread on greased 9 x 13-inch (or larger) baking sheet and refrigerate until cool.
Break into bite size pieces.
Makes a good gift.

title: crock-pot chicken gumbo
directions: First put layer of onion, celery and bell pepper in crock-pot. Add chicken and bay leaf.
Next, add rice, soup, water and file. Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours, or on high for 2 1/2 to 4 hours.
If it gets too dry, add a little boiling water.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together thoroughly sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, oil, eggs and salt.
Add to mixture pumpkin, baking soda, water and flour. Grease and flour 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill 3/4 full and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Combine cranberries and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until cranberry skins pop (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool.
Strain cranberry juice.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Strain and serve hot.

title: potato salad
directions: Beat the eggs in a saucepan on stove.
Add the sugar and vinegar; beat until thick and boiling.
Let cool.
Add Miracle Whip and mustard.
Add rest of ingredients as desired.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine sour cream, Worcestershire, celery and garlic salt and lemon juice.
Coat chicken, then roll in stuffing mix that has been crushed.
Place in baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: wassail cheer(serves 20)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except wine. Bring to boil, then simmer 10 minutes. Remove whole spices. Add wine and heat through. Serve in mugs and garnish, if desired, with apple slices. Makes about 20 servings.

title: homemade cake flour
directions: For each cup of cake flour you want, put 2 tablespoons cornstarch into a 1-cup measuring cup.
Spoon in enough all-purpose flour to reach the 1 cup mark.
Sift together 3 times.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix first nine ingredients and add bran flakes.
May be stored in refrigerator and keeps up to 6 weeks.
Do not freeze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut up beef and mix with onions and cream cheese.
Form in a ball.
Place in refrigerator.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer refried beans in container; mix seasoning and sour cream.
Place as next layer.
Layer lettuce and tomatoes.
Pour taco sauce on top and sprinkle with cheese.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl.
Add oil, apples and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Beat eggs until light color.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Fold egg mixture into apple mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli and cauliflower into pieces like you would for potato salad.
Add onion, Cheddar cheese and broken pieces of bacon.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and mix with mixture.
Refrigerate.
You can put Cheddar cheese on top when you serve it.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Layer in order as ingredients are listed.
Put sausage in after water, except for a small amount. Add the celery soup and chicken soup on top of sausage.
Put small amount of sausage on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In covered skillet, cook sausage links in 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes.
Drain off water.
Remove cover and brown sausage, turning frequently until cooked through.
Add oil, if necessary.
Remove sausages from pan and slice.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together for a tasty dessert.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter.
Mix with graham crackers and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Soften 2 sticks butter; add eggs and the powdered sugar; beat for no less than 15 minutes.
Spread over crust layer. Add the bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Place cherries on top.

title: fruit cocktail deluxe
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until very thick, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly, then add mustard.
When cool, add to fruit mixture.
Add marshmallows.
Grate cheese on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
You may dress it up with maraschino cherry bits on top.

title: lemon surprise cake
directions: Mix all together for four minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Add ingredients in a small roaster.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and stir.
Bake another hour.

title: carrots
directions: You put them in the oven and cook them for a long time.
Then you eat them.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook
and
drain
spaghetti.
Dice turkey and onion (if fresh).
Mix
turkey, cheese, soup, mushrooms, pimentos, milk, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce together.
Heat thoroughly. Can be served two ways:

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Mix cake as on box.
Pour into greased 14 x 20-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Make pudding using milk and adding cream cheese.
Beat together. Spread on cake.
Spread drained pineapple on top, then spread stiff Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and dot with cherries.

title: stew
directions: Thoroughly brown meat on all sides in hot fat. Add water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion, bay leaves and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: pumpkin bread #2
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin; mix well.
Combine flour, spice, soda and salt in a large bowl; make well in center. Pour pumpkin mix into well.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in nuts (and cranberries if using).

title: cheese sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add soup, Velveeta, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread on buns.
Top with Mozzarella.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: squash puppies
directions: Grate squash and onion.
Mix corn meal, flour, eggs and buttermilk (should be thick like hushpuppies).
Add squash, onions and cheese; mix well.
Shape like hushpuppies.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Press nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on box and pour over nuts and coconut.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and melted oleo.
Mix until creamy.
Spoon on cake by the tablespoons.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mini apple pizzas
directions: Roll or pat biscuits into 3 1/2-inch circles; place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
In a mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add apples and mix well. Spoon rounded tablespoonfuls onto biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix sugar and salt and set aside.
Mix warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar to about 110° for dry yeast or lukewarm for cake mix.
Add 2 packages of yeast to water and let stand 5 to 10 minutes (begins to foam).
Add Crisco shortening to sugar mixture and cream.
Pour boiling water (1 cup) over this mixture and beat until smooth.
Beat 4 eggs and add to shortening mixture.
Beat 1 cup flour in this and add the dissolved yeast.
Gradually add the rest of the flour and the 2 pound bag of flour.
Beat as you sift it in.
Scrape sides of bowl down and brush the top of the dough with melted butter.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: cheese lasagna
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion, carrot and garlic; brown lightly.
Add beef; brown lightly.
Puree the tomatoes; add to the meat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add butter, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: apricot delight
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Let set.
Add crushed pineapple, banana and marshmallows.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and ice with topping.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add applesauce, eggs and oil. Bake at 350 degrees for about 35-40 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add berries; stir until dissolved.
Add bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix remaining ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight to soften marshmallows.
Stir and spread on salad.

title: monkey bread bundt cake
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in greased Bundt pan, with nuts and margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set overnight before making sandwiches.
Cut sandwiches and serve as finger sandwiches.

title: pinecone cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
With a wooden spoon, fold in pineapple, coconut, carrots and pecans.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pepper hash
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt, celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over vegetables; mix well.
This will keep in the refrigerator for months.

title: neesee's hush brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for nuts.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 11 x 15-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Stir all dry ingredients; mix with the egg and milk. Beat in the butter and the berries.
Bake in pan in moderate oven.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and for 1 minute cook at a rolling boil.
Remove from heat, stir in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add coconut and/or pecans, if desired.
Drop on wax paper.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 3/4-inch cubes and dredge with flour which has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot fat.
Wheat meat is browned, add onions, mushrooms and garlic.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Heat automatic skillet to 350°; melt butter.
Add chicken and sprinkle both sides with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Turn heat to simmer.
Cover pan and cook for 10 minutes. Add the water.
Cover the pan and continue to cook until chicken is tender (about 15 minutes).
Add rice.
Pour enough water into broth to make 2 cups of liquid.
Add broth and remaining ingredients to chicken and rice in pan.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until moisture is absorbed and rice is fluffy. Stir in almonds, if desired.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the pancake/baking mix, sugar and butter. Mix together.
Add the milk, vanilla, salt and coconut.
Pour into a well-buttered pie dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until it is light brown on top and set (firm).

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt, butter and 2 cups of flour.
Stir with spoon.
Add 2 more cups of flour.
Turn out and knead dough until smooth (about 6 to 8 minutes).
Place in a buttered bowl and turn surface until coated with butter.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: caramel
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add brown sugar and salt. Stir until combined and add corn syrup.
Mix well and add condensed milk.
Keep mixture on medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 244°.
Use more than 1 thermometer as the mixture coats the thermometer and is not accurate when heavily coated. When correct temperature is reached, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Mix well and pour into oiled pan.
When cold, cut into squares, dip in chocolate or wrap in plastic wrap to keep moist.

title: mom's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and refrigerate.
Best to do 1 day ahead and refrigerate to let flavors permeate.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and cream well.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Shape into small balls and press down with a fork.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
about 3 dozen.

title: hearty french onion soup
directions: In large heavy saucepan, melt the margarine over moderate heat; add onions and cook, uncovered, until golden, 8 to 10 minutes.
Blend in sugar and flour and cook, stirring, 3 minutes longer.
Add beef broth, wine, thyme, bay leaf and pepper; heat to moderately high and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, about 6 minutes.
Adjust heat so the mixture bubbles gently; simmer, partly covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf; stir in brandy, if desired.
Preheat broiler; rub each piece of bread with the garlic and sprinkle with cheese.
Ladle the soup into 4 ovenproof bowls and float a piece of bread, cheese side up, in each one.
Place bowls in the broiler 4 to 6 inches from the heat and broil until the cheese is golden brown, about 2 minutes. Serves 4.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in alternately with apple-sugar mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Let stand in pan until quite cool.
Turn out on rack or frost in pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie dish with crust.
Set aside.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie dish.
Place second crust on top.
Slightly moisten edges of crust, then crimp with fork to seal.
Cut 6 to 8 slits in top crust to vent steam.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken, rice and spice dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large size 14 x 20-inch Reynolds Oven Cooking Bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add rice, tomatoes, mushrooms, celery, onion, water, basil, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Squeeze bag gently to blend ingredients. Brush chicken with oil.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and additional salt and pepper to taste.
Cut sausage links into thirds.
Arrange chicken and sausage pieces on top of rice mixture. Close bag with nylon tie.
Make six 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brisket
directions: Place brisket on large sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle seasonings on both sides.
Pour liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce over top.
Wrap securely and let stand 6 to 8 hours in the refrigerator.
Place foil wrapped meat (do not add liquid) in slow cooker or very low oven.
Cook 8 to 10 hours. Chill before slicing thin.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and soda; set aside.
Cream butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour and soda into mix. Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: "keftethes" - meat balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the water.
To make a fluffy mixture if too stiff, use the water to make it softer and fluffier.
Let it rest at least 1 hour, then roll into small balls in flour and fry slowly.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put zucchini, onion
and
pickling
salt in large bowl. Mix well and
refrigerate
overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Drain again
and
place in large kettle with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Pour
into	hot
pint
jars
and seal. Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: no seal pickles
directions: Fill 4 gallon churn with whole cucumbers.
Add 2 cups salt for each gallon of water.
Cover cucumbers with salt water and let stand 7 days.
Remove from churn.
Wash and slice.
Return to churn.
Mix alum and water to cover.
Let stand 2 nights.
Remove from churn and wash.
Return to churn and add vinegar to cover. Let stand overnight.

title: mt. everest salad
directions: Mix and chill Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice about 10 to 15 minutes.
Chill remaining ingredients after mixing.
Place cherry halves on top for decoration.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix noodles with mixture made from all other ingredients.
Cover with crumbled bread crumbs.
Melt butter; pour on top of bread crumbs.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut butter into flour mixture. Add eggs and mix into dough.
Dough should not be too sticky. Refrigerate dough overnight.
Roll dough (small pieces) to about 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into small squares and deep fry in oil. When dough is all fried, coat with hot honey.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Saute garlic, onion, celery and bell pepper in butter until wilted; add chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, crawfish tails, parsley and green onions.
Cook just long enough to heat well.
Mix with rice.
Serve as a side dish. This is very highly seasoned with pepper.
If you don't like it that hot, use less pepper and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and egg until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add flour mixture to chopped nuts and cut up cherries.
Add both mixtures together. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mamita's arroz con pollo
directions: Brown chicken in heavy casserole in oil.
Add saffron (salt and pepper to taste), curry, onions and garlic.
Place in 325° oven. Bake until chicken is done, about an hour.
Add in rice, crushed tomatoes, olives, capers and peas.
Serve when heated through. Great for a make ahead dish to serve the next day.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour.
Blend in butter.
Add pecans and sprinkle on potatoes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam. Mix all ingredients and pour in dish. Place chicken pieces on top. Brush chicken with oil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: perogie casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Cook potatoes and drain. Add 3/4 of cheese and 1 stick of oleo and mash. Cut onions into thin slices and separate them. Saute in 1 stick oleo. Layer in casserole 1 stick of melted butter in bottom of 9 x 13 dish, noodles next, potatoes next, sauteed onions and 1/4 cheese, cut into cubes on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chunky chicken melt
directions: Mix chicken, mayonnaise and celery.
On baking sheet, arrange muffin halves.
Top with tomato.
Divide chicken mixture evenly among muffin halves.
Top with cheese.
Broil 6 inches from heat 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 3.
Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: papa's homemade cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: wee lemon cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar and mix eggs. Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to butter mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Drop cake batter by teaspoons into greased and floured small muffin tins.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from muffin tins.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in 1-inch cubes. In a large saucepan, bring to a boil enough water to cover potatoes (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup of water).
Add potatoes.
Cover tightly and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Slowly fry bacon crisp.
Place on paper towels to drain and crumble.

title: sausage pimento pinwheel casserole
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, crumble and brown sausage. Add green pepper and onion; cook 1 minute.
Stir in flour until dissolved.
Gradually stir in milk and salt.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Pour into ungreased 3 quart casserole.

title: no rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in the oleo until tender.
Add flour and cook until thick.
Stir in water and continue to stir until mixture is thick.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Stir in broccoli.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: green tomato pepper relish
directions: Wash, chop and mix vegetables.
Peel onions.
Discard pepper seeds.
Add salt; let stand for several hours or overnight.
Drain liquid and discard.
Tie spices in a bag.
Combine all ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
Ladle boiling mixture into hot jars, seal at once and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 12 pints.

title: mystery salad(don't give away the secret.)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Adjust mayonnaise to taste. This salad is great with fried fish.

title: filled cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, flour and cream cheese. Chill a few hours.
Roll dough out.
Cut cookies with a glass. Fill half of circle with pie filling.
Fold over and seal edges. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: karron's cookie bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter until crumbly.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together Eagle milk, egg and vanilla.
Add chips, nuts and coconut to it; mix again.
Spread this over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: creamy potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Cook onions in melted butter until soft, but not brown.
Mix in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and mix to coat potatoes.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: kai-tun hed hom(chicken soup)
directions: Boil the chicken for 20 minutes.
Add dried black mushrooms, soaked in warm water (add this water also).
Over a few times, add soy sauce, oyster sauce, pepper, garlic and salt.
If you like hot food, put in some more pepper.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Combine cream of chicken soup, milk and American cheese in saucepan.
Cover over low heat until cheese melts, stir constantly.
Add pimentos and green chilies; set aside.
Soften tortillas in microwave.
Add Cheddar cheese to cooled beef.
Fill tortillas with beef mixture.
Roll to enclose filling.
Place in a dish.
Pour cheese mixture over enchiladas. Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Fold in blackberries. Pour into 2 baked pie shells or graham cracker pie crust.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Fold all together and place in bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Cook raisins and rice in water and salt (until water is gone).
Beat eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Add to rice and raisins.
Simmer until it thickens.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: nichole's swift spud soup spectacular
directions: For
each bowl cut up bananas and pour sugar over them. Then add bread crumbs and cold milk.
Serve immediately.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients, liquid and all.
Mix.
Let set in refrigerator several hours to mix flavors.
Take out and bring to room temperature before serving.

title: dirt
directions: Beat cream cheese until softened.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Set aside.
Beat pudding and milk until thickened.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla to pudding.
Fold the two mixtures together. Crush Oreo cookies in blender.
(Do 6 to 7 cookies at a time.) Line flowerpot with aluminum foil.
Layer in pot, beginning and ending with Oreo cookies.
Wrap plastic around stems of flowers and insert in pot.
Refrigerate.

title: red cabbage and potatoes
directions: Chop cabbage.
Melt fat and cook finely chopped onion until light brown, then add cabbage and heat through.
Add bay leaf and cloves, salt, vinegar, water and cut up apples.
Steam until done. Add sugar to taste and cornstarch to thicken.

title: reuben brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Arrange bread cubes on bottom of dish.
Coarsely shred corned beef with knife. Layer meat over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and pepper in bowl until well blended.
Pour over corned beef mixture. Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake casserole, covered, in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes, then uncovered for 10 minutes or until bubbly and puffed.
Serve immediately.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand at least 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add understanding, patience and listening.
Stir in personality.
Season to taste with humor. Blend well.
Place in a warm place.
Serve in individual molds. Savor the results.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Melt butter; cook scrambled eggs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with ham, bacon or sausage.
Mix milk and soup; pour on top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cover with foil until needed.
Can be made day before and kept in refrigerator.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: greek tzatziki
directions: Strain the cucumber for about 1 hour.
In a serving bowl, blend all prepared ingredients together and let set in refrigerator for about an hour.
When serving, drizzle some olive oil over the Tzatziki and serve as an appetizer or dip with bread as an accompaniment.

title: perfect potato salad
directions: Sprinkle cooked potatoes with salt, sugar, celery and vinegar. Add onion, celery and pickle.
Add mayonnaise; toss to mix.
Fold in eggs.
Chill well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased flat casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Prepare rice as label directs.
In a bowl with a fork, beat eggs and salt slightly.
In a nonstick skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons of hot salad oil, gently stir rice until well coated with oil.
Push rice to one side of skillet.
In same pan over medium-high heat heat 1 tablespoon of oil until very hot; pour in eggs.
Cook with spoon, stirring quickly and constantly until eggs are the size of peas and leave side of pan.
Mix eggs with rice. Stir in peas; heat through.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice together until smooth.
Place vanilla wafers in cupcake papers in cupcake pans and spoon cream cheese mixture over wafers.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add a spoonful of cherry or blueberry pie filling to each one.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown
beef until crumbly.
Stir in dry taco seasoning. Add tomatoes
and
corn;
bring to a soft boil, stirring frequently. Pour
into
a 2 quart casserole.
Carefully top with bread mix (instructions on package).
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes or until brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: hobo stew
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and green pepper in oil until onion is golden. Add beef and brown, stirring with fork to break up meat until cooked.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: *dreamy fruit salad
directions: Be sure to drain all canned fruit well.
(I put it all together in strainer and let it set for quite a while.) Prepare pudding as directed, substituting fruit juice for milk.
Cool pudding thoroughly.
Blend in prepared topping (I used Dream Whip), fruit cocktail, pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add bananas and other fresh fruit, as desired.
Serves 12.

title: cookie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil with spoon.
Looks like cookie dough, then add chocolate chips.

title: fish salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce, in bowl.
Mix well. Serve on bed of lettuce leaves.

title: brickle bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook and stir margarine and unsweetened chocolate over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat lightly with a wooden spoon, just until combined.
(Don't overbeat or brownies will rise too high, then fall.)
