Stir in flour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together sugar, egg yolks and cream cheese.
Whip the whipping cream and egg whites.
Fold each in creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and stir.
Put graham cracker crumbs on top and bottom and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: heath candy
directions: Place all ingredients in cast-iron skillet.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon 10 to 12 minutes until thick and bubbly (it smells burnt) and golden brown.
Spread onto buttered cookie sheet; spread thin.
Place 3 Hershey bars on top of hot candy. Spread to edges of candy and let cool and harden.
Break into pieces when cooled.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter and butter; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt the white coating in a microwave-safe bowl.
Dip balls in coating and place on waxed paper to harden.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
Use only tops of broccoli (cut small).
Julienne peppers and onions and slice radishes and carrot thin.
Mix together with tortellini and Parmesan and add dressing.

title: salsa
directions: Bring to a boil, cook 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 quarts.

title: dill dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with cold raw vegetables.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Heat buttermilk until warm. Add remaining ingredients. Mix and knead until spongy. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover with 2 cups crushed potato chips.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350° in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: spinach parmesan cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; set aside.
Heat butter; add flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Add nutmeg, garlic powder, salt and pepper and remove from heat.
Add 1/3 of hot mixture to egg yolks, stirring constantly, then stir back into remaining hot mixture.
Add cheese and spinach and mix.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into spinach mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: scratchey dunkey
directions: Boil the chicken until done; then debone and cube.
Cook noodles in chicken broth and drain.
Brown onion, celery and bell pepper in butter.
Add all together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top before baking.
May add grated cheese to top about 5 minutes before removing from oven, if desired.

title: date nut bars
directions: Blend shortening, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs, singly, beating well after each addition.
Pour boiling water over dates; let cool.
Add to creamed mixture and blend.
Sift soda with flour; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Spread in 10 x 20 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool; cut in bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop by spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into prepared crust.
Chill 2-3 hours.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together by hand.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Batter will be thick.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, vinegar and water.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at one time.
Blend with spoon just until all the flour is moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be re-rolled.
Yield: 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: biscotti
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter.
Spread in a greased 17 X 11 cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.	Cool.
Cut into bars and bake again at 450 degrees for a few more minutes. Drizzle with powdered sugar icing.

title: chile beans
directions: Brown meat and onions with seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add melted margarine.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake in a 350° oven about 40 to 50 minutes or until firm.

title: green chile rice
directions: Coat a skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onions.
Saute until tender.
Stir in rice and next 6 ingredients.
Add 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Spoon mixture into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: hot rolls
directions: Sandwich 2 Ritz crackers together with a generous amount of peanut butter.
Press together so peanut butter spreads to edge. Using tongs, dip crackers into melted almond bark (vanilla or chocolate).
Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix well and pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pickled hot peppers
directions: Wash peppers; slice in thick slices or leave whole, making holes in each pepper with toothpick or ice pick.
Cover peppers with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix vinegar, water, cooking oil and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Drain water off peppers and pack in jars.
Add the other salt and cooking oil to each jar and seal.
Makes very good peppers and pepper sauce.

title: corned beef pizza
directions: Mix flour and baking powder in bowl.
Add salad dressing and milk; mix until mixture forms ball.
Press into 14-inch pizza pan. Sprinkle with corned beef.
Mix cheese, sour cream and dry mustard in bowl.
Spread over corned beef.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: "100" sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter or margarine, oil, eggs, vanilla, salt, soda, and cream of tartar.
Add flour one cup at a time, mixing well after each cup.
Freeze dough and keep frozen between batches.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Press each cookie with the bottom of a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown. If cookies are not made too large, this will make 100 or more cookies.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and bake cornbread according to directions.
Remove from oven, cool and crumble.
Meanwhile cook sausage, crumbling as it cooks.
Drain off grease, wash with warm water and finish draining on paper towel.
Chop pickles, tomatoes, onions and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Stir in sausage and cornmeal.

title: easy turkey chili
directions: Spray saucepan with nonstick spray.
Add turkey, onions, green peppers and garlic.
Cook until turkey is lightly brown or done. Add beans, tomatoes (with juices), salsa, cumin and chili powder. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes to blend flavors.
If desired, top with Cheddar cheese or sour cream.

title: cornish game hens with orange marmalade
directions: Rinse hens thoroughly under running cold water.
Pat dry. Stuff hens with orange, lemon and lime slices and close cavity. Brush hens with oil and sprinkle with paprika.
Place hens on barbecue spit and cook on medium heat until juices run clear and meat feels tender (about 60 minutes).
Baste hens with orange marmalade during the last 1/2 of cooking time or at the last 15 minutes.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour, spices and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk and add gradually to first mixture.
Add prunes while still using mixer. Stir in nuts by hand with wooden spoon.
Bake in broiler pan at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and carrots. Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in coconut.
Drop dough by teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until no imprint remains when touched lightly.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Cool.
Frost with Orange Butter Icing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to the creamed mixture.
Chill dough in refrigerator a while.
Shape into small round balls.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: blueberry muffin cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and mix several minutes.
Add blueberries. Bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: candy shake
directions: Combine in a blender until mixed.
Pour into a glass.
Enjoy.

title: overnight rolls(a caramel hot roll delight!)
directions: Grease a 9-inch round cake pan, Bundt pan or angel food pan. Cut bread dough up in pieces and place in the bottom of pan. Sprinkle with pudding mix.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1 white until thick.
Add milk; beat again. Add lime juice (fresh or bottled), beating until thick.
Fold in 3 beaten egg whites; add few drops of coloring (if desired).
Pour into cooked pie shell.
(Graham cracker crust may be used.)
Bake 15 minutes at 250° or until set.
Refrigerate.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, lemon juice, vanilla and cream cheese in blender or with a mixer until smooth.
Stir in the cranberry sauce.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Thaw 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: egg-cheese-meat brunch
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add cheese. Add layer of sausage.
Then pour mixture of milk, soup and eggs over sausage.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Divide cookie crumbs; using one half of crumbs, pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Layer slices of ice cream on crumbs. Freeze. Remove from freezer and drizzle fudge topping over the ice cream. Spread whipped topping over fudge topping. Sprinkle the remaining cookie crumbs on top. Place in freezer until ready to serve. Serves 15 to 18.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Bake as directed in 2 round pans.
Cream together cheese, cool whip and sugar.
Fold in 8 candy bars. Spread on cake.
Top with remaining candy bars.
Press candy around sides.

title: apple salad dressing
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups water.
Mix the next three ingredients and stir into boiling water.
Cook 3 minutes and add oleo, salt, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour this over apples.

title: bonnie's marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine; add marshmallows.
Stir and add Jell-O mix. Pour over popped corn.
Mix.
Shape into balls.
Wrap with Saran Wrap and tie.

title: orange bright salad
directions: Wash, dry and tear romaine into bite-sized pieces.
Slice mushrooms and toss with lettuce.
Add herbs and toss again.
Chill in refrigerator.
While preparing remaining ingredients slice peeled oranges into 1/4-inch slices or use mandarin oranges.
Slice onion thinly.
Heat almonds and sugar in heavy skillet.
Toss and heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Sugar should be melted, forming a glaze over the almonds.
Cool.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a heavy large skillet.
Saute vegetables 30 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add crawfish tails and fat. Saute for 1 minute and stir in flour.
Continue sauteing 3 minutes, then add water, chicken bouillon cubes and parsley. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add 1/2 packet seasoning mix with 1/2 cup water.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and pour into a greased pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quart relish
directions: Chop, mix and drain excess liquid.
Put in large skillet; add handful of mixed pickling spices.
Boil until translucent.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, corn, butter and salt.
Mix well and turn into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 325° until set (1 hour).

title: cranberry-orange relish (uncooked)
directions: Put berries, unpeeled oranges and cored apples through food chopper or food processor.
Add sugar; let stand overnight.
Put in sterilized cans and lids and refrigerate.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Season meat.
Add onion, rice and eggs.
Roll a portion of filling into each leaf.
Fasten ends with toothpicks.
Place rolls in pressure cooker. Pour soup and water over rolls.
Cover; let pressure build and cook for 8 minutes.
Reduce pressure normally. Serves 8.

title: sauerkraut ham balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine ham, sauerkraut, onion and 2 tablespoons of the bread crumbs.
In another bowl, combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic powder and pepper; stir into sauerkraut mixture.
Chill for at least 1 hour or overnight. Shape into 3/4-inch balls; coat with flour.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Dip ham balls into the egg mixture, then roll in the remaining bread crumbs.
Heat oil to 375° in a deep fat fryer or electric skillet; fry ham balls until golden brown.
Drain. Yield:
60 appetizers.

title: frozen pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Pour mixture into popsicle molds.
Freeze for 3 hours or more.
Hold molds under warm water for a few seconds to loosen pops.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt shortening in cast-iron skillet.
Mix corn meal, flour, egg and milk all together.
Add to hot skillet.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes.

title: rosie's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil big enough chicken to get 4 cups chopped chicken.
Save the broth from boiling.
Chop onion, celery and carrots.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour; stir in pineapple juice.
Beat eggs with lemon juice and add to flour mixture (mixing well).
Cook over low heat until thick and let cool.
In a large bowl, combine fruit. Pour cool custard mixture over fruit and coat well.
Combine grated cheese and coconut; spread on top of salad.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: clam fritters
directions: Make a batter of flour, baking powder, salt, milk, clam liquor and well beaten eggs.
Chop clams; season with salt and pepper. Add to the batter and drop by tablespoons into deep fat; brown until done.

title: fried chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover chops with soup.
Reduce heat to simmer and continue to cook, covered for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: poppin fresh bar-b-cup
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large skillet, brown beef and drain. Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Set aside.
Separate biscuit dough into 12 biscuits.
Place one biscuit in each of 12 ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough up sides to each of cup. Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Work in shortening, vinegar and water. Cut in rounds and roll for any kind of fruit pies.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Place into pre-lined candy mold and cap.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add salt and baking powder; sift again.
Add flour and milk to creamed mixture, alternately.
When mixture becomes smooth, add vanilla.
Pour into cake pans and bake at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup Milnot with caramels; set aside.
Mix dry cake mix with 3/4 cup butter and 1/3 cup Milnot.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1/2 cake mixture in pan and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Spread caramel mixture over top.
Put 1 cup chocolate chips over this.
Next, add 1 cup pecans.
Spread other half cake mixture over everything.
Bake 18 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco 100% Bran.
Cream remaining ingredients together.
Mix well and bake in greased muffin pans or use muffin papers.
Bake 20 minutes in 400°
oven.
Yields about 60 muffins.

title: almond cappuccino
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine coffee, milk and sugar.
Stirring occasionally, cook over medium-high heat until mixture begins to boil; remove from heat.
Stir in extracts. Serve hot.
Yield: about sixteen 6 ounce servings.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix peanut butter with honey.
Add crushed pecans or walnuts. Add 1/2 cup powdered milk.
Mix well.
Sprinkle in remaining powdered milk on waxed paper.
Shape mixture in a roll in waxed paper.
Refrigerate.
Eat in slices.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add egg and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: margie gessaman's sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Return meat and onion to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: creamed vegetables
directions: Cook all frozen vegetables together until tender.
Drain. Cream together chicken and cheese soups.
Add a small amount of milk to soup to thin.
Combine all ingredients and reheat.

title: jumbo shells seafood fancies
directions: Add shells gradually to 6 quarts boiling salted water; cook until tender yet firm.
Drain; rinse with cold water, then drain again.
Invert on paper towel-lined plate to cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Place fruit pie filling in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch cake pan.
Place pineapple on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pineapple.
Cut up oleo on top of the mix.
Cover the top with pecans (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spud spice cake
directions: Combine sugar, potatoes, shortening, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Cream 4 minutes.
Add eggs; blend well.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Coat nuts with 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir into batter.

title: chicken breast a l'orange
directions: Shake chicken breasts in paper sack with flour and seasonings until evenly coated.
Heat shortening in a 10-inch skillet over medium-high flame.
Place floured chicken in hot fat, skin side down.
When brown, turn and continue to fry, until well browned on both sides.
Pour off fat.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and simmer over low flame for 1 hour or until chicken and carrots are tender.
If serving is delayed, lower flame to "warm" setting to keep just right for serving. Yield:
4 servings.

title: tasty muffins
directions: Spray muffin pan with cooking oil.
Spray or line with paper muffin cups.
Stir ingredients together just until moistened.
Add blueberries, raspberries or cherries, grated lemon peel and almond slices.

title: orange chicken
directions: In large, nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, heat oil. Add chicken and brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add red pepper, onion and garlic and saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add orange juice, mustard, salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes. Transfer chicken to serving platter; keep warm.

title: four day coconut cake
directions: The night before baking, combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Mix chicken soup and chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Arrange mixed vegetables over this.
Mix flour and baking powder in separate bowl.
Add buttermilk and butter.
Stir to form a thin dough, pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until crust rises to top and browns lightly.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together
and
pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey-glazed turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Remove the skin from the turkey breast and discard. Place the breast in a roaster pan. Season with salt and pepper. In a small bowl mix together the honey, Dijon mustard and rosemary. Pour half of the glaze over the turkey breast and bake, uncovered, for about 2 hrs., or until meat thermometer registers 170 to 175° when placed in the thickest part of the breast. You may want to add a little water to the pan, if needed. During the final 15 minutes of baking, brush the remaining glaze over the turkey breast.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add a little flour and eggs alternately and mix after each addition.
(Beat eggs up before adding to butter and sugar.)
Cook at 300 degrees for approximately 1 hour.

title: broccoli bleu cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Meanwhile, blend butter with flour, salt and cheeses in saucepan.
Add milk all at once and cook until thickened.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into 1-quart casserole and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook, bone and dice chicken into bite sized pieces.
Mix chicken, 1 can soup, 1/2 of cheese, chilies, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Divide evenly (about 3 tablespoonfuls) among the tortillas.
Roll up and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour other can of soup over tortillas.
Put rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple marmalade
directions: Remove orange and lemon peels with a vegetable peeler.
Cut into very thin strips.
In a medium saucepan combine peels and pineapple juice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not drain.
Cut white membranes off fruit.
Section fruit over a bowl to catch juices.
Discard seeds.
Add fruits and juices to peel mixture.
Simmer, covered 10 minutes more.
Add undrained pineapple.
Transfer fruit mixture to Dutch oven (8 quarts).
Stir in pectin.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in sugar.
Return to full rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly skim off foam.
Ladle at once into hot, clean 1/2 pint canning jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Wipe rims, adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Start timing after water boils.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add coloring.
Beat one egg at a time into mixture.
Mix buttermilk, vinegar, and baking soda.
Add to above mixture.
Beat until it gets creamy.
Pour into 2 prepared 9 inch cake pans.
Bake at 375 degrees until toothpick comes back clean.

title: norwegian cheese soup
directions: In large pan cook celery, onion and green pepper until tender. Add the soup and milk with water and vegetables.
In double boiler combine tomato paste, coriander, pepper and cheese until smooth.
Add mixture to original pot.
Simmer until mixed and add sour cream.

title: miriam's favorite microwaved shrimp and rice
directions: Heat butter and oil in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish, uncovered, at full heat in microwave for 3 minutes.
Add scallions, celery, parsley and rice.
Stir.
Cook at full power 4 minutes.
Stir in broth.
Cook at full power for 12 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables and cook 12 more minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes with loose cover.
Sprinkle with cheese and eat.

title: pickle relish
directions: Pare cukes.
Cut lengthwise; discard seeds and pulp.
Dice cukes.
Peel onions and dice.
Cut peppers and dice.
Combine vegetables.
Stir in salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water; drain again.
Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery and mustard seed.
Cook slowly until cukes are transparent, but not mushy.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish.
Top this with the following mixture.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: In large bowl, add Cool Whip, oranges, pineapple, cottage cheese and jello.
Combine all ingredients well with spoon.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
You can also use fruit cocktail in place of oranges and use mixed fruit jello in place of orange jello.

title: salad for a luncheon
directions: Mix together the shrimp, peas, celery and onion.
Mix together the mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce and salt.
Add to shrimp and vegetables.
Just before serving, add the chow mein noodles and the roasted slivered almonds.
Garnish with a sliced hard-boiled egg.

title: fish and vegetable bake(serves 6)
directions: Arrange onions on bottom of large baking pan.
Place fish steaks on top of onions; dot with 2 tablespoons of butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour on tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Add well drained vegetables.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake for 20 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Put celery, green pepper, onion, butter and garlic in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for
10 to 12 minutes, stirring once, until vegetables are crisp
tender.
Stir
in flour just until blended, then add the juice,
soup and salt.
Cover and microwave on High 3 to
minutes
until
sauce thickens slightly. Stir in remaining ingredients
except lemon wedges.
Cover and microwave on High 5 to
minutes,
stirring twice, until the shrimp are pink and barely opaque in center.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate at least 24 hours.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Beat in double boiler over boiling water until spreading consistency.
Will frost 2 layer cake top to side.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and lime jello in water.
When jello is set a little, add 7-Up.
In a separate bowl mix pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Blend into jello mixture and let set to harden. Dissolve strawberry jello and the 1 cup hot water.
Pour over top of set jello.
When jello is set a little, beat whipped cream and cream cheese until smooth and slightly thickened.
Pour on top of jello and let set.
Serve cooled.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise then crosswise in 1/4-inch slices.
Coat cookie sheet with cooking spray.
Dip eggplant in egg whites, then bread crumbs to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and drizzle with oil.
Wrap garlic and onion in foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, turning eggplant once. Mix the tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and sugar in a non-stick medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove garlic and onion from oven; squeeze garlic from skin into tomato mixture; add the onion.
Lower heat; simmer 15 minutes.
Spread 3/4 cup sauce evenly over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towel to remove excess moisture.
Press into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Combine the ham, cheese and green peppers; spoon over crust.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over all.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes before cutting.
This will reheat well.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add flavorings, then sift dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and brandy. Blend well.
Put into 3-quart mold and bake in slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack. Delicious!

title: chicken breast and mushroom in madeira sauce
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet, add chicken and brown over medium-high heat for about 10 minutes on each side. Sprinkle both sides with salt and pepper.
Transfer to a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Trim mushrooms, toss with lemon juice and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to skillet, stir in shallots and saute for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes or until slightly brown, stirring often.
Blend in flour, pour in wine, then add cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Mix in 1/2 cup of cheese.
Spoon sauce over chicken, sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is bubbly and tender.
Serves 6.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve both jellos in 2 cups hot water.
Add cold water. Add bananas, marshmallows and drained pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Cook sugar, egg, flour and 1 cup of reserved pineapple juice until thickened.
Spread over congealed jello.
Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip (almost a whole small container).
Spread over second layer of jello.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Serves about 10.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and warm except tortillas or Tostitos.
Layer in long cake pan the tortillas or Tostitos and hamburger mixture.
Bake about 30 to 45 minutes; can be put in microwave.
Top with Ro-Tel cheese dip.
Makes a big casserole dish.
If you like a drier dish, add more Tostitos.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour; mix well.
Gradually add milk until slightly thickened. Add cheese; cook until melted.
Add to broth with chicken.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut up and place in bottom of dish. Chop onion and place over chicken.
Dice Velveeta cheese and put half on top of onion.
Crush up Doritos and put half on top of cheese.
Mix together in a bowl, Ro-Tel and soups.
Pour on top of Doritos.
Put the other half of crushed Doritos on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Dredge chicken in sour cream; roll in crumbs.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and celery salt.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix and let set overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Roll balls in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375°.

title: lard pie crust
directions: Combine lard, flour and salt.
Beat egg in cup and add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Combine with vinegar and mix.

title: chop suey
directions: Cover beef, molasses and
soy sauce with water and stew until tender.
Add
Chinese
vegetables and bean sprouts.
Add mushrooms.	Serve over Chinese noodles or rice.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a loaf and place in roasting pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: christmas odor punch(not for drinking)
directions: Place ingredients in large old kettle.
Allow to come to a boil for several minutes. Turn to simmer. Add water as needed. Can be saved and reused.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Slice cream cheese into small pieces.
Place in microwave-safe baking dish.
Pour chili over cream cheese.
Microwave, loosely covered, on High for 5 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Microwave, loosely covered, for 2 to 3 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.
Yield:
80 servings.

title: aunt atha's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and stir into mixture.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan.

title: horseradish carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender-crisp.
Reserve 1/4 cup liquid. Combine onion, mayonnaise, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Add liquid; put carrots into 1 1/2-quart casserole; fold in mixture. Cover with crumbs.
Dot with oleo.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain (can also brown with onion).
Pour can of soup over meat in casserole dish.
Layer cheese over the soup.
Add layer of Tater Tots.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 375° or until Tater Tots are golden brown.

title: easy toffee bars
directions: Combine sugar and butter and bring to a boil.
Place the graham crackers on buttered, foil-lined cookie sheet and pour the sugar mixture over them.
Bake in a 400° oven for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and pour the chips over the top and spread evenly.
Pour the nuts over the top and press in.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: ice cream roll and raspberry sauce
directions: Beat eggs, salt and vanilla at medium speed until frothy. Continue to beat as you add 1/2 cup sugar slowly and beat until mixture is light, thick and smooth.
While beater takes care of eggs and sugar, do these 3 things:

title: yummy stuff(child's one-pot meal)
directions: Cook pasta in water seasoned with the bouillon.
Drain. Return to
pot and add cheese slice.
Cover.
Let cheese melt and
mix in
meat
and vegetables.
Serve with ketchup on the side.
Serves 2 children.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split wings in joints.
Drain tips, if desired.
Pat dry. Deep fry at 400° (high) until crisp, 12 minutes.
Remove; drain. Combine the red hot sauce and butter.
Toss wings to cover completely.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir oil and vanilla together.
Stir flour, cocoa, salt, warm water, vinegar, sugar and soda; slowly add in other mixture. Blend, but do not beat.
Mixture will be runny.
Pour into ungreased pan and bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. Needs no frosting.
This is very moist chocolate cake.
Travels well - great for picnics.
Simply delicious!

title: cranberry-apple drink
directions: In large pitcher, combine juice concentrates, water, lemon juice and apple slices.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice cubes.
Makes six 8 ounce servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and cook in medium saucepan over medium heat; bring to a boil and boil for exactly 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Spoon onto wax paper, cool, then eat!

title: potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook at 350° in partly baked pie crust until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole. Top with 1 stick butter and crushed corn flakes. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese snaps
directions: Cream butter and cheese well.
Add flour, red pepper, salt and pecans.
Mix well.
Form into small logs and wrap in foil.
Leave in refrigerator until hard enough to slice.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch closely.
For cheese sticks, use pastry bag to form stick.
Chill, then bake same as before.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to instructions on the box.
Let it cool.
Then poke it with a toothpick or fork and make holes all over the cake.
Mix the jello with 1 cup of boiling water and 1 cup of cold strawberry pop, then pour all over the cake.
Make sure you get the corners.
Then mix the vanilla pudding according to instructions and the Dream Whip according to the directions on the box and mix them together and ice the cake with it.
(Some people use Cool Whip to ice the cake, then refrigerate for at least two hours before serving.)

title: sausage and bread crumb stuffing
directions: Crumble sausage meat and brown in skillet. Remove sausage and saute onion and celery in part of fat and butter or margarine. Combine the seasonings and bread crumbs.
Toss together with onion mixture and sausage.
If a moist dressing is desired, add enough liquid to moisten crumbs.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak navy beans overnight.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 2 hours or more.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until mixture is light green in color.
Chill and serve.

title: cream cheese appetizer
directions: Place cream cheese block (room temperature) on a serving platter.
Pour chile salsa over the block so it covers the block. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: baked apple pudding with rum
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sift first 5 ingredients.
With mixer at cream, mix butter with sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Grate apples, medium fine.
Measure 2 cups.
Add to egg mixture.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture just until mixed.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Store in pan.
Cut into 8 squares.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix jello, milk, coconut and extract.
Shape like strawberries.
Make red sugar by dropping 1 to 2 drops of red food color into white sugar.
Roll strawberries in sugar.
Color almonds green with green food coloring.
Put 2 almonds into top of strawberry for leaf.

title: stack cake
directions: *Add enough sugar and allspice to suit your taste for between layers.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: orange-pecan salad
directions: Peel banana; cut in quarters lengthwise and again crosswise. Roll in pecans.
Peel oranges; cut in slices crosswise and remove the center core.
Insert a cube of banana in center of each slice. Arrange on a bed of lettuce.
Sprinkle over remainder of pecans and French dressing.
Makes eight portions.

title: chicken with apricot jelly and wish-bone dressing
directions: Place chicken pieces in a pan, skin side up.
Mix rest of ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste 3 or 4 times the last 1/2 hour.

title: dad's chicken marsala
directions: Cut chicken in 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Roll in bread crumbs coating all sides.
Heat skillet and melt butter.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Cover chicken with wine (about 1 to 1 1/2 cups).
Let simmer until wine cooks out.
Turn chicken over and add garlic powder and salt to taste.
Cover with wine again and simmer until liquid is half.

title: taco casserole(for microwave)
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
May be done in microwave or in skillet on top of stove.
Mix everything together, except save a little cheese to sprinkle on top after putting in casserole dish. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Let set at least 5 minutes before serving.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Set oven at 375°.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add softened shortening, eggs and half the bananas. Beat until creamy, about 2 minutes, by hand.
Fold in remainder of bananas, rolled oats and walnuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake about 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Mix well. Stir in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in 3 tablespoons melted margarine.
Spoon into baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons melted margarine and pecans in a bowl.
Mix with fingers until crumbly.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: vegetable-bean burritos
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil; bake at 350° about 12 minutes or until heated through. In 10-inch skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil 5 minutes or until softened, stirring occasionally. Add bell peppers; cook 2 minutes. Partially mash one can of beans with wooden spoon or potato masher.

Add mashed beans, remaining can of beans, salsa and cumin to skillet; cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded cheese down center of each warmed tortilla. Spoon bean mixture over cheese. Top with cilantro, if desired, then roll up. Makes 4 servings.

title: beef taco dish
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix meat, salsa, mayonnaise and corn. In baking dish, place mixture, about 1/2.
Cover with crumbled taco chips.
Cover with cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with a salad.

title: oklahoma cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add eggs and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on bread and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly; roll into 1-inch balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 50 appetizers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook the pre-soaked beans in a saucepot for about 1 to 2 hours in plenty of water with the salt, bay leaf and oregano.
Remove them from the heat when they are soft but not mushy, as they will continue to cook in the stew.
Drain the beans, set aside and save the broth.
Peel, seed and chop the tomatoes and reserve juice. Open the chili pods and remove the seeds and veins; then, cut the chiles into narrow strips.
Cut the squash into large pieces. Shave the kernels from the corn.
Set chiles, squash and corn aside.

title: blitz torte or kiss me cake
directions: Cream shortening; beat in sugar and salt, then egg yolks, vanilla, milk and flour, mixed with baking powder.
Spread mixture in 2 round greased cake pans.
Beat egg whites until very light, adding 3/4 cup sugar slowly and spread on unbaked mixture in both pans.
Sprinkle nuts, sugar and cinnamon and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool and put together with whipped cream, berries or pudding.

title: apple custard coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix baking mix, sugar, oleo and milk.
Spread in pan.
Arrange apples on mixture in pan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix sour cream and egg.
Drizzle over top.
Bake until edges are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
